{"type":"message","id":"89b3bca0","parentId":"54ee96c2","timestamp":"2026-07-08T02:07:11.426Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e70bb8293bf740978d87495f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"AstroHub v8.37 - ��ƽ��ģ��\n\n������\n- IterativeWB: ���㷨��������\n- WhiteBalanceSearcher: ִ�в㣨��ͼ���������桢��֤��SSE�¼���\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport asyncio\nfrom .region_base import _rgb_stats, calc_stable_delay\n\n\n# ������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n# ���㷨�㣺��������\n# ������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n\nclass IterativeWB:\n    \"\"\"��ƽ����������� - R/B ��������\n    \n    ״̬���ֵ�(��5) �� �е�(��2) �� ����(��1)\n    ÿ������ [˫ͨ��, ��R, ��B] ������ѡ��ѡ delta ��С��\n    ȫ��׷�� best_gains + best_delta������ʱ�ع�����ѡ�\n    \n    ���룺BGRͼ��\n    �����dict��action, red_gain, blue_gain, delta, message�ȣ�\n    \n    ���漰�κ��豸������������ѧ�߼���\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, current_red=100, current_blue=100):\n        self._stage = 0\n        self._stage_steps = [5, 2, 1]\n        # v8.63: �׶�������ֵ - �ֵ�delta<=100, �е�delta<10, ����delta<0.1\n        self._stage_thresholds = [100, 10, 0.1]\n        self._current_red = current_red\n        self._current_blue = current_blue\n        self._no_improve = 0\n        self._stage_step_count = 0\n        self._fine_steps = 0\n        self._best_red = current_red\n        self._best_blue = current_blue\n        self._best_delta = 999.0\n        self._best_step = 0\n        self._step_count = 0\n\n    def _eval(self, r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, red, blue) -> float:\n        \"\"\"����RGBƽ��̶�\"\"\"\n        if g_sum < 1: g_sum = 1\n        ar = max(1, r_sum) * red / max(1, self._current_red)\n        ab = max(1, b_sum) * blue / max(1, self._current_blue)\n        return abs(ar / g_sum - 1.0) + abs(ab / g_sum - 1.0)\n\n    def step(self, bgr) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"����BGRͼ�񣬷�����һ������\"\"\"\n        stats = _rgb_stats(bgr)\n        n = stats[\"n\"]\n        r_sum, g_sum, b_sum = stats[\"r_sum\"], stats[\"g_sum\"], stats[\"b_sum\"]\n\n        self._step_count += 1\n        self._stage_step_count += 1\n        step = self._stage_steps[self._stage]\n\n        # �����ѡ����\n        cr = self._current_red + max(-step, min(step, int(g_sum / max(1, r_sum) * self._current_red) - self._current_red))\n        cb = self._current_blue + max(-step, min(step, int(g_sum / max(1, b_sum) * self._current_blue) - self._current_blue))\n        cr = max(1, min(255, cr))\n        cb = max(1, min(255, cb))\n\n        # ��ѡ�б� (- stage 2: R/B��������)\n        if self._stage == 2:\n            # �����׶Σ�ȫ��R/B��������\"both\"��ѡ\n            candidates = [(cr, self._current_blue, \"red\"), (self._current_red, cb, \"blue\")]\n        else:\n            candidates = [(cr, cb, \"both\"), (cr, self._current_blue, \"red\"), (self._current_red, cb, \"blue\")]\n\n        # ѡ���ź�ѡ\n        best_cand = None\n        best_d = 999.0\n        for r, b, label in candidates:\n            d = self._eval(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, r, b)\n            if d < best_d:\n                best_d = d\n                best_cand = (r, b, label)\n\n        new_red, new_blue, direction = best_cand\n        new_red = int(new_red)\n        new_blue = int(new_blue)\n\n        # ���㵱ǰdelta\n        actual = abs(r_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0)\n\n        # ����best\n        prev_best = self._best_delta\n        if actual < self._best_delta:\n            self._best_delta = actual\n            self._best_red = self._current_red\n            self._best_blue = self._current_blue\n            self._best_step = self._step_count\n\n        # �޸��Ƽ���\n        tolerance = 0.95  # v8.63: ͳһ���̶�\n        if actual >= prev_best * tolerance:\n            self._no_improve += 1\n        else:\n            self._no_improve = 0\n\n        stage_name = [\"coarse\", \"medium\", \"fine\"][self._stage]\n\n        # v8.63: �׶����� - ����delta��ֵ\n        # �ֵ����е�: delta <= 100\n        # �е�������: delta < 10\n        if self._stage < 2 and actual <= self._stage_thresholds[self._stage]:\n            self._stage += 1\n            self._stage_step_count = 0\n            self._no_improve = 0\n            # ���뾫��ʱ����best׷��\n            if self._stage == 2:\n                self._best_delta = 999.0\n                self._best_red = self._current_red\n                self._best_blue = self._current_blue\n                self._best_step = self._step_count\n            return {\n                \"action\": \"continue\",\n                \"stage\": [\"medium\", \"fine\"][self._stage - 1],\n                \"step_size\": self._stage_steps[self._stage],\n                \"red_gain\": self._current_red, \"blue_gain\": self._current_blue,\n                \"r_avg\": round(stats[\"r_avg\"], 1), \"g_avg\": round(stats[\"g_avg\"], 1), \"b_avg\": round(stats[\"b_avg\"], 1),\n                \"delta\": round(actual, 4), \"best_delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"pixels\": n,\n                \"message\": f\"����{'�е�' if self._stage == 1 else '��ϸ'}��У (step=��{self._stage_steps[self._stage]})\"\n            }\n\n        # �����׶δ��� - ����20����delta<0.1\n        if self._stage == 2:\n            self._fine_steps += 1\n            if self._fine_steps >= 20 or actual < 0.1:\n                rollback = (self._best_red != self._current_red or self._best_blue != self._current_blue)\n                self._current_red = self._best_red\n                self._current_blue = self._best_blue\n                return {\n                    \"action\": \"stop\",\n                    \"stage\": \"done\",\n                    \"step_size\": 0,\n                    \"red_gain\": self._best_red, \"blue_gain\": self._best_blue,\n                    \"r_avg\": round(stats[\"r_avg\"], 1), \"g_avg\": round(stats[\"g_avg\"], 1), \"b_avg\": round(stats[\"b_avg\"], 1),\n                    \"delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"best_delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"pixels\": n,\n                    \"message\": f\"��ƽ����� {'(�ع������)' if rollback else '(�Ѵ����)'} ��{self._best_step}��\"\n                }\n\n        # Ӧ��������\n        self._current_red = new_red\n        self._current_blue = new_blue\n        return {\n            \"action\": \"continue\",\n            \"stage\": stage_name,\n            \"step_size\": step,\n            \"red_gain\": new_red, \"blue_gain\": new_blue,\n            \"r_avg\": round(stats[\"r_avg\"], 1), \"g_avg\": round(stats[\"g_avg\"], 1), \"b_avg\": round(stats[\"b_avg\"], 1),\n            \"delta\": round(actual, 4), \"best_delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"pixels\": n,\n            \"message\": f\"{'��' if self._stage == 0 else '��' if self._stage == 1 else '��'}�� {direction} (��{step})\"\n        }\n\n\n# ������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n# ִ�в㣺Э���豸����\n# ������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n\nclass WhiteBalanceSearcher:\n    \"\"\"��ƽ������ִ����\n    \n    ����\n    - �л��ֶ���ƽ��ģʽ\n    - ��ȡ��ǰ����\n    - ��ȡ��ѡ����\n    - ����IterativeWB.step()\n    - Ӧ�����浽�豸\n    - �л�������ƽ��ģʽ\n    - ��֤���\n    - ����SSE�¼�\n    \n    �����κ��㷨���ߣ�ִֻ�С�\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, mgr, device_ip, client, x, y, w, h, capture_func, cleanup_func, mac_clean=\"\"):\n        self.mgr = mgr\n        self.device_ip = device_ip\n        self.client = client\n        self.x = x\n        self.y = y\n        self.w = w\n        self.h = h\n        self._capture_func = capture_func\n        self._cleanup_func = cleanup_func\n        self._interrupted = False  # v8.41: �жϱ�־\n        self._mac_clean = mac_clean  # v8.47: ���ڱ�������\n        self._stable_delay = 1.5  # v8.64: �����ӳٻ��棬������ʼʱ��һ��\n    \n    def _set_wb_mode(self, mode: str):\n        \"\"\"���ð�ƽ��ģʽ: manual/locked\"\"\"\n        xml = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<WhiteBalance version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n<WhiteBalanceStyle>{mode}</WhiteBalanceStyle>\n</WhiteBalance>'''\n        resp = self.client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\", xml)\n        return resp.status_code == 200\n    \n    def _set_wb_gains(self, red: int, blue: int):\n        \"\"\"���ð�ƽ������\"\"\"\n        xml = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<WhiteBalance version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n<WhiteBalanceStyle>manual</WhiteBalanceStyle>\n<WhiteBalanceRed>{red}</WhiteBalanceRed>\n<WhiteBalanceBlue>{blue}</WhiteBalanceBlue>\n</WhiteBalance>'''\n        resp = self.client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\", xml)\n        return resp.status_code == 200\n    \n    def _read_wb_status(self):\n        \"\"\"��ȡ��ǰ��ƽ��״̬��ģʽ+���棩- v8.62\"\"\"\n        try:\n            resp = self.client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\")\n            if resp.status_code == 200:\n                import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n                root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n                mode = \"auto\"\n                red, blue = 100, 100\n                for elem in root.iter():\n                    tag = elem.tag.split('}')[-1] if '}' in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                    if tag in (\"WhiteBalanceStyle\", \"whiteBalanceStyle\"):\n                        mode = (elem.text or \"auto\").lower()\n                    elif tag in (\"WhiteBalanceRed\", \"whiteBalanceRed\"):\n                        red = int(elem.text)\n                    elif tag in (\"WhiteBalanceBlue\", \"whiteBalanceBlue\"):\n                        blue = int(elem.text)\n                return mode, red, blue\n        except:\n            pass\n        return \"auto\", 100, 100\n    \n    def _capture(self):\n        \"\"\"��ȡ��ѡ����\"\"\"\n        bgr, crop_path, info = self._capture_func(\n            self.client, self.mgr, self.device_ip, \"WB\",\n            self.x, self.y, self.w, self.h,\n            skip_delay=True  # v8.64: run() �ѵȴ�\n        )\n        return bgr, info\n    \n    def _interrupt(self):\n        \"\"\"v8.41: �жϰ�ƽ������\"\"\"\n        self._interrupted = True\n    \n    async def run(self):\n        \"\"\"���а�ƽ������������SSE�¼�\"\"\"\n        \n        # v8.64: �����ӳ�ֻ��һ��\n        self._stable_delay = await asyncio.to_thread(calc_stable_delay, self.client)\n        \n        # 1. ��ȡ��ǰģʽ+���棨v8.62��\n        current_mode, current_red, current_blue = await asyncio.to_thread(self._read_wb_status)\n        \n        # 2. �л��ֶ���ƽ��ģʽ\n        ok = await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_mode, \"manual\")\n        if not ok:\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'warning', 'message': '�л��ֶ���ƽ��ʧ��'})}\\n\\n\"\n        \n        # 3. ��ʼֵ�ж�\n        if current_mode == \"auto\":\n            # �Զ�ģʽ �� ��50/50�𲽣�д���豸\n            current_red, current_blue = 50, 50\n            await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, 50, 50)\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'info', 'message': '��ʼֵ: R=50, B=50'})}\\n\\n\"\n        else:\n            # locked/manual ģʽ �� �ӵ�ǰֵ��ʼ�������ϴ�����/������ɣ�\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'info', 'message': f'��ʼֵ: R={current_red}, B={current_blue}'})}\\n\\n\"\n        \n        # 4. ��ʼ��ͼ��v8.62 ����ԭ���߼���\n        bgr, info = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n        if bgr is None:\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'error', 'message': '��ͼʧ��'})}\\n\\n\"\n            return\n        \n        crop_msg = f\"X={info['crop_x1']}~{info['crop_x2']}, Y={info['crop_y1']}~{info['crop_y2']}, ��{info['pixels']}����\"\n        yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'start', 'crop': crop_msg, 'initial_red': current_red, 'initial_blue': current_blue})}\\n\\n\"\n        \n        # 4. ��ƽ��ѭ��\n        wb = IterativeWB(current_red, current_blue)\n        step_count = 0\n        \n        while True:\n            # v8.41: ����ж�\n            if self._interrupted:\n                # v8.62: �� IterativeWB ʵ����ȡ best ֵ\n                best_red = wb._best_red\n                best_blue = wb._best_blue\n                # д��bestֵ������\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, best_red, best_blue)\n                await asyncio.sleep(self._stable_delay)\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_mode, \"locked\")\n                \n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({\n                    'type': 'interrupt',\n                    'message': '�û�ֹͣ',\n                    'final_red': best_red,\n                    'final_blue': best_blue\n                })}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n            \n            cmd = wb.step(bgr)\n            step_count += 1\n            \n            # ���Ͳ����¼�\n            event = {\n                \"type\": \"wb\",\n                \"step\": step_count,\n                \"stage\": cmd.get(\"stage\", \"\"),\n                \"step_size\": cmd.get(\"step_size\", 0),\n                \"red_gain\": cmd[\"red_gain\"],\n                \"blue_gain\": cmd[\"blue_gain\"],\n                \"r_avg\": cmd.get(\"r_avg\", 0),\n                \"g_avg\": cmd.get(\"g_avg\", 0),\n                \"b_avg\": cmd.get(\"b_avg\", 0),\n                \"delta\": cmd.get(\"delta\", 0),\n                \"best_delta\": cmd.get(\"best_delta\", 0),\n                \"message\": cmd[\"message\"]\n            }\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps(event)}\\n\\n\"\n            \n            # ֹͣ��\n            if cmd[\"action\"] == \"stop\":\n                # Ӧ����������\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, cmd[\"red_gain\"], cmd[\"blue_gain\"])\n                await asyncio.sleep(self._stable_delay)\n                \n                # ��֤\n                bgr2, _ = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n                verified_delta = cmd.get(\"best_delta\", cmd.get(\"delta\", 0))\n                \n                if bgr2 is not None:\n                    stats = _rgb_stats(bgr2)\n                    r_sum, g_sum, b_sum = stats[\"r_sum\"], stats[\"g_sum\"], stats[\"b_sum\"]\n                    verified_delta = abs(r_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0)\n                \n                # �л�������ƽ��ģʽ\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_mode, \"locked\")\n                \n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'done', 'final_red': cmd['red_gain'], 'final_blue': cmd['blue_gain'], 'best_delta': round(cmd.get('best_delta', 0), 4), 'verified_delta': round(verified_delta, 4), 'total_steps': step_count, 'message': '�л�������ƽ��'})}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n            \n            # Ӧ������\n            await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, cmd[\"red_gain\"], cmd[\"blue_gain\"])\n            await asyncio.sleep(self._stable_delay)  # �ȴ��ȶ�\n            \n            # ���½�ͼ\n            bgr, _ = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n            if bgr is None:\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'error', 'message': '��ͼʧ��'})}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n        \n        # 5. ����\n        await asyncio.to_thread(self._cleanup_func, \"WB\", self.device_ip)\n        yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'cleanup'})}\\n\\n\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":360,"aggregated":"\"\"\"AstroHub v8.37 - ��ƽ��ģ��\n\n������\n- IterativeWB: ���㷨��������\n- WhiteBalanceSearcher: ִ�в㣨��ͼ���������桢��֤��SSE�¼���\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport asyncio\nfrom .region_base import _rgb_stats, calc_stable_delay\n\n\n# ������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n# ���㷨�㣺��������\n# ������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n\nclass IterativeWB:\n    \"\"\"��ƽ����������� - R/B ��������\n    \n    ״̬���ֵ�(��5) �� �е�(��2) �� ����(��1)\n    ÿ������ [˫ͨ��, ��R, ��B] ������ѡ��ѡ delta ��С��\n    ȫ��׷�� best_gains + best_delta������ʱ�ع�����ѡ�\n    \n    ���룺BGRͼ��\n    �����dict��action, red_gain, blue_gain, delta, message�ȣ�\n    \n    ���漰�κ��豸������������ѧ�߼���\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, current_red=100, current_blue=100):\n        self._stage = 0\n        self._stage_steps = [5, 2, 1]\n        # v8.63: �׶�������ֵ - �ֵ�delta<=100, �е�delta<10, ����delta<0.1\n        self._stage_thresholds = [100, 10, 0.1]\n        self._current_red = current_red\n        self._current_blue = current_blue\n        self._no_improve = 0\n        self._stage_step_count = 0\n        self._fine_steps = 0\n        self._best_red = current_red\n        self._best_blue = current_blue\n        self._best_delta = 999.0\n        self._best_step = 0\n        self._step_count = 0\n\n    def _eval(self, r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, red, blue) -> float:\n        \"\"\"����RGBƽ��̶�\"\"\"\n        if g_sum < 1: g_sum = 1\n        ar = max(1, r_sum) * red / max(1, self._current_red)\n        ab = max(1, b_sum) * blue / max(1, self._current_blue)\n        return abs(ar / g_sum - 1.0) + abs(ab / g_sum - 1.0)\n\n    def step(self, bgr) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"����BGRͼ�񣬷�����һ������\"\"\"\n        stats = _rgb_stats(bgr)\n        n = stats[\"n\"]\n        r_sum, g_sum, b_sum = stats[\"r_sum\"], stats[\"g_sum\"], stats[\"b_sum\"]\n\n        self._step_count += 1\n        self._stage_step_count += 1\n        step = self._stage_steps[self._stage]\n\n        # �����ѡ����\n        cr = self._current_red + max(-step, min(step, int(g_sum / max(1, r_sum) * self._current_red) - self._current_red))\n        cb = self._current_blue + max(-step, min(step, int(g_sum / max(1, b_sum) * self._current_blue) - self._current_blue))\n        cr = max(1, min(255, cr))\n        cb = max(1, min(255, cb))\n\n        # ��ѡ�б� (- stage 2: R/B��������)\n        if self._stage == 2:\n            # �����׶Σ�ȫ��R/B��������\"both\"��ѡ\n            candidates = [(cr, self._current_blue, \"red\"), (self._current_red, cb, \"blue\")]\n        else:\n            candidates = [(cr, cb, \"both\"), (cr, self._current_blue, \"red\"), (self._current_red, cb, \"blue\")]\n\n        # ѡ���ź�ѡ\n        best_cand = None\n        best_d = 999.0\n        for r, b, label in candidates:\n            d = self._eval(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, r, b)\n            if d < best_d:\n                best_d = d\n                best_cand = (r, b, label)\n\n        new_red, new_blue, direction = best_cand\n        new_red = int(new_red)\n        new_blue = int(new_blue)\n\n        # ���㵱ǰdelta\n        actual = abs(r_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0)\n\n        # ����best\n        prev_best = self._best_delta\n        if actual < self._best_delta:\n            self._best_delta = actual\n            self._best_red = self._current_red\n            self._best_blue = self._current_blue\n            self._best_step = self._step_count\n\n        # �޸��Ƽ���\n        tolerance = 0.95  # v8.63: ͳһ���̶�\n        if actual >= prev_best * tolerance:\n            self._no_improve += 1\n        else:\n            self._no_improve = 0\n\n        stage_name = [\"coarse\", \"medium\", \"fine\"][self._stage]\n\n        # v8.63: �׶����� - ����delta��ֵ\n        # �ֵ����е�: delta <= 100\n        # �е�������: delta < 10\n        if self._stage < 2 and actual <= self._stage_thresholds[self._stage]:\n            self._stage += 1\n            self._stage_step_count = 0\n            self._no_improve = 0\n            # ���뾫��ʱ����best׷��\n            if self._stage == 2:\n                self._best_delta = 999.0\n                self._best_red = self._current_red\n                self._best_blue = self._current_blue\n                self._best_step = self._step_count\n            return {\n                \"action\": \"continue\",\n                \"stage\": [\"medium\", \"fine\"][self._stage - 1],\n                \"step_size\": self._stage_steps[self._stage],\n                \"red_gain\": self._current_red, \"blue_gain\": self._current_blue,\n                \"r_avg\": round(stats[\"r_avg\"], 1), \"g_avg\": round(stats[\"g_avg\"], 1), \"b_avg\": round(stats[\"b_avg\"], 1),\n                \"delta\": round(actual, 4), \"best_delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"pixels\": n,\n                \"message\": f\"����{'�е�' if self._stage == 1 else '��ϸ'}��У (step=��{self._stage_steps[self._stage]})\"\n            }\n\n        # �����׶δ��� - ����20����delta<0.1\n        if self._stage == 2:\n            self._fine_steps += 1\n            if self._fine_steps >= 20 or actual < 0.1:\n                rollback = (self._best_red != self._current_red or self._best_blue != self._current_blue)\n                self._current_red = self._best_red\n                self._current_blue = self._best_blue\n                return {\n                    \"action\": \"stop\",\n                    \"stage\": \"done\",\n                    \"step_size\": 0,\n                    \"red_gain\": self._best_red, \"blue_gain\": self._best_blue,\n                    \"r_avg\": round(stats[\"r_avg\"], 1), \"g_avg\": round(stats[\"g_avg\"], 1), \"b_avg\": round(stats[\"b_avg\"], 1),\n                    \"delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"best_delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"pixels\": n,\n                    \"message\": f\"��ƽ����� {'(�ع������)' if rollback else '(�Ѵ����)'} ��{self._best_step}��\"\n                }\n\n        # Ӧ��������\n        self._current_red = new_red\n        self._current_blue = new_blue\n        return {\n            \"action\": \"continue\",\n            \"stage\": stage_name,\n            \"step_size\": step,\n            \"red_gain\": new_red, \"blue_gain\": new_blue,\n            \"r_avg\": round(stats[\"r_avg\"], 1), \"g_avg\": round(stats[\"g_avg\"], 1), \"b_avg\": round(stats[\"b_avg\"], 1),\n            \"delta\": round(actual, 4), \"best_delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"pixels\": n,\n            \"message\": f\"{'��' if self._stage == 0 else '��' if self._stage == 1 else '��'}�� {direction} (��{step})\"\n        }\n\n\n# ������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n# ִ�в㣺Э���豸����\n# ������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������\n\nclass WhiteBalanceSearcher:\n    \"\"\"��ƽ������ִ����\n    \n    ����\n    - �л��ֶ���ƽ��ģʽ\n    - ��ȡ��ǰ����\n    - ��ȡ��ѡ����\n    - ����IterativeWB.step()\n    - Ӧ�����浽�豸\n    - �л�������ƽ��ģʽ\n    - ��֤���\n    - ����SSE�¼�\n    \n    �����κ��㷨���ߣ�ִֻ�С�\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, mgr, device_ip, client, x, y, w, h, capture_func, cleanup_func, mac_clean=\"\"):\n        self.mgr = mgr\n        self.device_ip = device_ip\n        self.client = client\n        self.x = x\n        self.y = y\n        self.w = w\n        self.h = h\n        self._capture_func = capture_func\n        self._cleanup_func = cleanup_func\n        self._interrupted = False  # v8.41: �жϱ�־\n        self._mac_clean = mac_clean  # v8.47: ���ڱ�������\n        self._stable_delay = 1.5  # v8.64: �����ӳٻ��棬������ʼʱ��һ��\n    \n    def _set_wb_mode(self, mode: str):\n        \"\"\"���ð�ƽ��ģʽ: manual/locked\"\"\"\n        xml = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<WhiteBalance version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n<WhiteBalanceStyle>{mode}</WhiteBalanceStyle>\n</WhiteBalance>'''\n        resp = self.client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\", xml)\n        return resp.status_code == 200\n    \n    def _set_wb_gains(self, red: int, blue: int):\n        \"\"\"���ð�ƽ������\"\"\"\n        xml = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<WhiteBalance version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n<WhiteBalanceStyle>manual</WhiteBalanceStyle>\n<WhiteBalanceRed>{red}</WhiteBalanceRed>\n<WhiteBalanceBlue>{blue}</WhiteBalanceBlue>\n</WhiteBalance>'''\n        resp = self.client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\", xml)\n        return resp.status_code == 200\n    \n    def _read_wb_status(self):\n        \"\"\"��ȡ��ǰ��ƽ��״̬��ģʽ+���棩- v8.62\"\"\"\n        try:\n            resp = self.client.get(\"/Image/channels/1/whiteBalance\")\n            if resp.status_code == 200:\n                import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n                root = ET.fromstring(resp.xml)\n                mode = \"auto\"\n                red, blue = 100, 100\n                for elem in root.iter():\n                    tag = elem.tag.split('}')[-1] if '}' in elem.tag else elem.tag\n                    if tag in (\"WhiteBalanceStyle\", \"whiteBalanceStyle\"):\n                        mode = (elem.text or \"auto\").lower()\n                    elif tag in (\"WhiteBalanceRed\", \"whiteBalanceRed\"):\n                        red = int(elem.text)\n                    elif tag in (\"WhiteBalanceBlue\", \"whiteBalanceBlue\"):\n                        blue = int(elem.text)\n                return mode, red, blue\n        except:\n            pass\n        return \"auto\", 100, 100\n    \n    def _capture(self):\n        \"\"\"��ȡ��ѡ����\"\"\"\n        bgr, crop_path, info = self._capture_func(\n            self.client, self.mgr, self.device_ip, \"WB\",\n            self.x, self.y, self.w, self.h,\n            skip_delay=True  # v8.64: run() �ѵȴ�\n        )\n        return bgr, info\n    \n    def _interrupt(self):\n        \"\"\"v8.41: �жϰ�ƽ������\"\"\"\n        self._interrupted = True\n    \n    async def run(self):\n        \"\"\"���а�ƽ������������SSE�¼�\"\"\"\n        \n        # v8.64: �����ӳ�ֻ��һ��\n        self._stable_delay = await asyncio.to_thread(calc_stable_delay, self.client)\n        \n        # 1. ��ȡ��ǰģʽ+���棨v8.62��\n        current_mode, current_red, current_blue = await asyncio.to_thread(self._read_wb_status)\n        \n        # 2. �л��ֶ���ƽ��ģʽ\n        ok = await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_mode, \"manual\")\n        if not ok:\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'warning', 'message': '�л��ֶ���ƽ��ʧ��'})}\\n\\n\"\n        \n        # 3. ��ʼֵ�ж�\n        if current_mode == \"auto\":\n            # �Զ�ģʽ �� ��50/50�𲽣�д���豸\n            current_red, current_blue = 50, 50\n            await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, 50, 50)\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'info', 'message': '��ʼֵ: R=50, B=50'})}\\n\\n\"\n        else:\n            # locked/manual ģʽ �� �ӵ�ǰֵ��ʼ�������ϴ�����/������ɣ�\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'info', 'message': f'��ʼֵ: R={current_red}, B={current_blue}'})}\\n\\n\"\n        \n        # 4. ��ʼ��ͼ��v8.62 ����ԭ���߼���\n        bgr, info = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n        if bgr is None:\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'error', 'message': '��ͼʧ��'})}\\n\\n\"\n            return\n        \n        crop_msg = f\"X={info['crop_x1']}~{info['crop_x2']}, Y={info['crop_y1']}~{info['crop_y2']}, ��{info['pixels']}����\"\n        yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'start', 'crop': crop_msg, 'initial_red': current_red, 'initial_blue': current_blue})}\\n\\n\"\n        \n        # 4. ��ƽ��ѭ��\n        wb = IterativeWB(current_red, current_blue)\n        step_count = 0\n        \n        while True:\n            # v8.41: ����ж�\n            if self._interrupted:\n                # v8.62: �� IterativeWB ʵ����ȡ best ֵ\n                best_red = wb._best_red\n                best_blue = wb._best_blue\n                # д��bestֵ������\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, best_red, best_blue)\n                await asyncio.sleep(self._stable_delay)\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_mode, \"locked\")\n                \n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({\n                    'type': 'interrupt',\n                    'message': '�û�ֹͣ',\n                    'final_red': best_red,\n                    'final_blue': best_blue\n                })}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n            \n            cmd = wb.step(bgr)\n            step_count += 1\n            \n            # ���Ͳ����¼�\n            event = {\n                \"type\": \"wb\",\n                \"step\": step_count,\n                \"stage\": cmd.get(\"stage\", \"\"),\n                \"step_size\": cmd.get(\"step_size\", 0),\n                \"red_gain\": cmd[\"red_gain\"],\n                \"blue_gain\": cmd[\"blue_gain\"],\n                \"r_avg\": cmd.get(\"r_avg\", 0),\n                \"g_avg\": cmd.get(\"g_avg\", 0),\n                \"b_avg\": cmd.get(\"b_avg\", 0),\n                \"delta\": cmd.get(\"delta\", 0),\n                \"best_delta\": cmd.get(\"best_delta\", 0),\n                \"message\": cmd[\"message\"]\n            }\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps(event)}\\n\\n\"\n            \n            # ֹͣ��\n            if cmd[\"action\"] == \"stop\":\n                # Ӧ����������\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, cmd[\"red_gain\"], cmd[\"blue_gain\"])\n                await asyncio.sleep(self._stable_delay)\n                \n                # ��֤\n                bgr2, _ = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n                verified_delta = cmd.get(\"best_delta\", cmd.get(\"delta\", 0))\n                \n                if bgr2 is not None:\n                    stats = _rgb_stats(bgr2)\n                    r_sum, g_sum, b_sum = stats[\"r_sum\"], stats[\"g_sum\"], stats[\"b_sum\"]\n                    verified_delta = abs(r_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0)\n                \n                # �л�������ƽ��ģʽ\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_mode, \"locked\")\n                \n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'done', 'final_red': cmd['red_gain'], 'final_blue': cmd['blue_gain'], 'best_delta': round(cmd.get('best_delta', 0), 4), 'verified_delta': round(verified_delta, 4), 'total_steps': step_count, 'message': '�л�������ƽ��'})}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n            \n            # Ӧ������\n            await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, cmd[\"red_gain\"], cmd[\"blue_gain\"])\n            await asyncio.sleep(self._stable_delay)  # �ȴ��ȶ�\n            \n            # ���½�ͼ\n            bgr, _ = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n            if bgr is None:\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'error', 'message': '��ͼʧ��'})}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n        \n        # 5. ����\n        await asyncio.to_thread(self._cleanup_func, \"WB\", self.device_ip)\n        yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'cleanup'})}\\n\\n\"","cwd":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783476431426}}
{"type":"message","id":"891ab691","parentId":"89b3bca0","timestamp":"2026-07-08T02:08:24.960Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"...\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"老板，问题找到了。\n\n---\n\n## 问题分析\n\n### 根本原因：`_eval()` 与 `actual` 使用不同的 delta 计算公式\n\n**`_eval()`**（用于选择最佳候选）：\n```python\nar = r_sum * red / self._current_red\nab = b_sum * blue / self._current_blue\nreturn abs(ar / g_sum - 1.0) + abs(ab / g_sum - 1.0)\n```\n→ 基于**比例推算**，会随 red/blue 变化而**单调递减**\n\n**`actual`**（用于判断是否改善）：\n```python\nactual = abs(r_sum / g_sum - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / g_sum - 1.0)\n```\n→ 基于**原始像素值**，不受增益影响\n\n### 问题链：\n1. `_eval()` 认为每一步都有改善（因为是比例值，越调越接近）\n2. 但 `actual`（实际白平衡状态）在后期**没有真正改善**\n3. `actual` 从不触发 `actual >= prev_best * 0.95` 的回退条件\n4. **best 始终被更新**，但更新的是 `actual` 值，不是 `_eval` 值\n5. 39步后，算法认为\"已完成\"，回退到 best = R=95, B=21（起始值）\n\n### 为什么 B=21 不变？\n\n日志中 `fine` 阶段（#19-#39），B 始终是 21：\n```\n#19: fine R=114 B=21 → R=135.6 G=12.7 B=9.4\n#20: fine R=113 B=21 → R=140.8 G=12.6 B=8.3\n...\n#39: fine R=95  B=21 → R=130.9 G=33.1 B=8\n```\n\n这说明 `cb`（候选蓝色）计算结果 = 21（被 clamp 到最小值），即：\n```\ncb = current_blue + clamp(g_sum / b_sum * current_blue - current_blue, -step, step)\n   = 21 + clamp(...) = 21\n```\n→ `g_sum / b_sum * current_blue - current_blue ≈ 0`，说明 **G ≈ B 的比例关系**，但 R/G 差距巨大（R=130 vs G=33）\n\n---\n\n## 修复方案\n\n### 方案A：统一 delta 公式（推荐）\n\n将 `_eval()` 改为与 `actual` 相同的公式，使用真实像素差值：\n\n```python\ndef _eval(self, r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, red, blue) -> float:\n    \"\"\"评估RGB平衡度 - 使用真实像素差值\"\"\"\n    if g_sum < 1: g_sum = 1\n    if r_sum < 1: r_sum = 1\n    if b_sum < 1: b_sum = 1\n    # 模拟调整后 R/B 与 G 的差值\n    # 调整后 r_avg ≈ r_sum * red / current_red (比例放大)\n    # 但更准确的是直接用 r_sum/g_sum 与 1 的差距\n    # 候选选择时，需要考虑当前增益对实际成像的影响\n    ar = r_sum * red / max(1, self._current_red) / g_sum\n    ab = b_sum * blue / max(1, self._current_blue) / g_sum\n    return abs(ar - 1.0) + abs(ab - 1.0)\n```\n\n问题在于 `_eval` 的归一化方式。当前代码：\n```python\nar = max(1, r_sum) * red / max(1, self._current_red)\n```\n这里 `r_sum` 是像素总和（可能很大），而 `g_sum` 也是。相除后比例是对的，但...\n\n等等，让我重新看：\n\n```python\nar = max(1, r_sum) * red / max(1, self._current_red)\nab = max(1, b_sum) * blue / max(1, self._current_blue)\nreturn abs(ar / g_sum - 1.0) + abs(ab / g_sum - 1.0)\n```\n\n这实际上是：`|r_sum * red / (current_red * g_sum) - 1| + |b_sum * blue / (current_blue * g_sum) - 1|`\n\n而 `actual` 是：`|r_sum / g_sum - 1| + |b_sum / g_sum - 1|`\n\n**差异在于 `_eval` 包含了 red/blue 增益的修正因子**，而 `actual` 没有。\n\n这意味着：\n- `_eval` 会随着 red 增益增大而认为 R 通道更平衡\n- 但 `actual` 只看原始像素，不管增益\n- 所以 `_eval` 可以\"骗过\"自己，认为调整有效，但 `actual` 不变\n\n### 方案B：修复 best 追踪逻辑\n\n核心问题：`best` 应该追踪 `_eval` 的最小值，而不是 `actual` 的最小值。当前代码：\n```python\nactual = abs(r_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0)\nif actual < self._best_delta:\n    self._best_delta = actual\n```\n\n但候选选择用的是 `_eval`：\n```python\nd = self._eval(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, r, b)\n```\n\n这两个公式不一致，导致最佳追踪失效。\n\n### 建议修复：将 `_eval` 和 best 追踪统一为同一公式\n\n**方案B1：都用 actual 公式**\n\n修改 `_eval` 使其与 `actual` 一致，并在 best 追踪中也使用 `_eval`：\n\n```python\ndef _eval(self, r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, red, blue) -> float:\n    \"\"\"评估RGB平衡度 - 与actual一致\"\"\"\n    if g_sum < 1: g_sum = 1\n    ar = max(1, r_sum) * red / max(1, self._current_red)\n    ab = max(1, b_sum) * blue / max(1, self._current_blue)\n    # 归一化到 g_sum\n    return abs(ar / g_sum - 1.0) + abs(ab / g_sum - 1.0)\n\n# 在 step() 中：\neval_current = self._eval(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, self._current_red, self._current_blue)\nif eval_current < self._best_delta:\n    self._best_delta = eval_current\n    self._best_red = self._current_red\n    self._best_blue = self._current_blue\n```\n\n但这还是有同样的问题... \n\n让我重新分析日志。\n\n看 #39 和最终状态：\n```\n#39: fine R=95 B=21 → R=130.9 G=33.1 B=8 (Δ=3.7094)\n```\n\nR=130.9, G=33.1, B=8\n\n这是**调整后**的像素平均值。说明 R 远大于 G 和 B。\n\n如果目标是 R≈G≈B，那么 R=130, G=33, B=8 显然没达到。\n\n但 `actual = |130.9/33.1 - 1| + |8/33.1 - 1| = |3.95 - 1| + |0.24 - 1| = 2.95 + 0.76 = 3.71`\n\n嗯，Δ=3.7094 和这个计算一致。\n\n所以 `actual` 公式本身是对的，它反映了 R/G/B 的实际差距。\n\n问题是：**为什么算法认为 3.7 是\"最佳\"？**\n\n看 #14：R=142, G=8.4, B=8 → Δ=15.98\n看 #39：R=130.9, G=33.1, B=8 → Δ=3.71\n\n从 #14 到 #39，R 从 142→130.9（下降），G 从 8.4→33.1（上升），B 保持 8。\n\nG 上升说明画面变亮了（增益或曝光变化），但 R 和 B 的绝对值变化不大。\n\n**等等！** 这里有个关键问题：\n\n`actual` 公式是 `|R/G - 1| + |B/G - 1|`\n\n如果 G 从 8.4 上升到 33.1（亮度增加），那么：\n- R/G 从 142/8.4=16.9 降到 130.9/33.1=3.95\n- B/G 从 8/8.4=0.95 降到 8/33.1=0.24\n\n所以 Δ 下降是因为**亮度变化**，不是因为白平衡改善！\n\n这就是根本问题：**算法用 R/G 和 B/G 的差距来评估白平衡，但这个指标受亮度影响很大。亮度增加会导致指标\"虚假改善\"。**\n\n---\n\n## 最终分析\n\n### 核心问题\n\n`actual = |R/G - 1| + |B/G - 1|` 这个公式**不独立于亮度**。\n\n当画面亮度增加时（比如自动曝光补偿），G 增大，R/G 和 B/G 都下降，Δ 看起来改善，但实际上白平衡没变好。\n\n### 修复方案\n\n**方案A：使用归一化比例**\n\n白平衡应该关注 **R:G:B 的相对比例**，而不是绝对值。\n\n正确的公式应该是：\n```python\n# 归一化到总和\ntotal = r_sum + g_sum + b_sum\nif total < 1: total = 1\nr_ratio = r_sum / total\ng_ratio = g_sum / total  \nb_ratio = b_sum / total\n# 目标：R:G:B = 1:1:1，即各占 1/3\ndelta = abs(r_ratio - 1/3) + abs(g_ratio - 1/3) + abs(b_ratio - 1/3)\n```\n\n或者更简单的：\n```python\n# R:G:B 应该接近 1:1:1\n# 用 R/G 和 B/G 的比值，但要消除亮度影响\n# 正确方法：比较 R_avg 和 B_avg 相对于 G_avg 的\"色温偏移\"\n# 而不是绝对差值\nr_ratio = r_sum / g_sum  # R/G 比值\nb_ratio = b_sum / g_sum  # B/G 比值\n# 理想情况：r_ratio ≈ 1, b_ratio ≈ 1\n# 但实际白平衡中，R/G/B 不一定相等，取决于光源\n# 目标是最小化 R:G:B 的方差\n```\n\n实际上，白平衡的目标是**消除色偏**，让白色物体显示为白色。这通常需要：\n1. 识别参考白色/灰色\n2. 调整 R/B 增益使 R=G=B\n\n但当前算法假设\"目标状态是 R=G=B\"，这在非中性光源下可能不正确。\n\n不过对于天文设备，假设目标是中性白，修复方案是：\n\n**方案A：归一化比例（推荐）**\n\n```python\ndef _eval(self, r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, red, blue) -> float:\n    \"\"\"评估RGB平衡度 - 使用归一化比例\"\"\"\n    total = r_sum + g_sum + b_sum\n    if total < 1: total = 1\n    # 模拟调整后的比例\n    r_after = r_sum * red / max(1, self._current_red)\n    b_after = b_sum * blue / max(1, self._current_blue)\n    total_after = r_after + g_sum + b_after\n    # 各通道占比\n    r_ratio = r_after / total_after\n    g_ratio = g_sum / total_after\n    b_ratio = b_after / total_after\n    # 目标：各占 1/3\n    return abs(r_ratio - 1/3) + abs(g_ratio - 1/3) + abs(b_ratio - 1/3)\n```\n\n同样修改 `actual`：\n```python\ntotal = r_sum + g_sum + b_sum\nif total < 1: total = 1\nr_ratio = r_sum / total\ng_ratio = g_sum / total\nb_ratio = b_sum / total\nactual = abs(r_ratio - 1/3) + abs(g_ratio - 1/3) + abs(b_ratio - 1/3)\n```\n\n这样无论亮度如何变化，算法都能正确评估白平衡状态。\n\n---\n\n老板，以上是完整分析和修复方案。请确认是否按方案A实施？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":6,"output":2926,"cacheRead":26610,"cacheWrite":6529,"totalTokens":36071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783476431427,"responseId":"msg_3fd61291-9346-48ed-b2a4-9ce6ddafcec0"}}
