{"type":"message","id":"6eec0d81","parentId":"2b3acc56","timestamp":"2026-07-08T02:32:33.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why B is stuck at 21. Let me re-read the code carefully to understand this.\n\nLooking at the candidate generation in `step()`:\n\n```python\ncr = self._current_red + max(-step, min(step, int(g_sum / max(1, r_sum) * self._current_red) - self._current_red))\ncb = self._current_blue + max(-step, min(step, int(g_sum / max(1, b_sum) * self._current_blue) - self._current_blue))\n```\n\nSo for B:\n- `cb = current_blue + clamp(int(g_sum / b_sum * current_blue) - current_blue, -step, step)`\n\nAt step 39, the image values are R=130.9, G=33.1, B=8.\n\nLet me calculate:\n- `g_sum / b_sum * current_blue = 33.1 / 8 * 21 = 4.1375 * 21 = 86.89`\n- `int(86.89) = 86`\n- `86 - 21 = 65`\n- `clamp(65, -1, 1) = 1` (since step=1 in fine stage)\n- So `cb = 21 + 1 = 22`\n\nNow let's check `_eval` for the three candidates:\n1. `(cr, current_blue, \"red\")` - adjust R only\n2. `(current_red, cb, \"blue\")` - adjust B only\n3. `(cr, cb, \"both\")` - adjust both (not in fine stage)\n\nWait, in fine stage (stage 2), the code says:\n```python\nif self._stage == 2:\n    candidates = [(cr, self._current_blue, \"red\"), (self._current_red, cb, \"blue\")]\n```\n\nSo only two candidates: adjust R or adjust B.\n\nFor candidate 1 (adjust R):\n- `cr = 95 + clamp(int(33.1/130.9 * 95) - 95, -1, 1)`\n- `= 95 + clamp(int(0.253 * 95) - 95, -1, 1)`\n- `= 95 + clamp(int(24.03) - 95, -1, 1)`\n- `= 95 + clamp(24 - 95, -1, 1)`\n- `= 95 + clamp(-71, -1, 1)`\n- `= 95 + (-1) = 94`\n\nFor candidate 2 (adjust B):\n- `cb = 21 + clamp(int(33.1/8 * 21) - 21, -1, 1)`\n- `= 21 + clamp(int(86.89) - 21, -1, 1)`\n- `= 21 + clamp(86 - 21, -1, 1)`\n- `= 21 + clamp(65, -1, 1)`\n- `= 21 + 1 = 22`\n\nNow evaluate both candidates with `_eval`:\n```python\ndef _eval(self, r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, red, blue) -> float:\n    ar = max(1, r_sum) * red / max(