\"R=95 B=21\" = the gain values BEFORE the adjustment\n- \"R=130.9 G=33.1 B=8\" = the image values AFTER the adjustment\n\nSo at step 38, the gains were R=95, B=21 (from step 37's output), and after adjustment, the image is R=133.5, G=32, B=8.\n\nAt step 39, the gains are still R=95, B=21 (from step 38's output? But step 38 shows the same gains...).\n\nI'm confused. Let me look at the code to understand the log format.\n\nActually, looking at the code, the `step()` method returns:\n```python\nreturn {\n    \"action\": \"continue\",\n    \"stage\": stage_name,\n    \"step_size\": step,\n    \"red_gain\": new_red, \"blue_gain\": new_blue,\n    \"r_avg\": round(stats[\"r_avg\"], 1), \"g_avg\": round(stats[\"g_avg\"], 1), \"b_avg\": round(stats[\"b_avg\"], 1),\n    \"delta\": round(actual, 4), \"best_delta\": round(self._best_delta, 4), \"pixels\": n,\n    \"message\": f\"{'粗' if self._stage == 0 else '中' if self._stage == 1 else '细'}级 {direction} (±{step})\"\n}\n```\n\nSo `red_gain` and `blue_gain` are the NEW gain values after the adjustment.\nAnd `r_avg`, `g_avg`, `b_avg` are the current image values (before applying the new gains).\n\nSo the log format \"R=95 B=21 → R=130.9 G=33.1 B=8\" means:\n- R=95, B=21 = the new gain values\n- R=130.9, G=33.1, B=8 = the current image values (from the screenshot taken before this step)\n\nSo at step 38, the algorithm chose R=95, B=21 (from step 37's gains? No, step 38 is a new adjustment).\n\nWait, I think I'm overcomplicating this. Let me re-read the log:\n\n```\n[09:52:41] ◇ 调整 #37: fine R=96 B=21 → R=135.6 G=31 B=8 (Δ=4.1203)\n[09:52:43] ◇ 调整 #38: fine R=95 B=21 → R=133.5 G=32 B=8 (Δ=3.9213)\n[09:52:45] ◇ 调整 #39: done R=95 B=21 → R=130.9 G=33.1 B=8 (Δ=3.7094)\n```\n\nStep 37: new gains = R=96, B=21; image = R=135.6, G=31, B=8\nStep 38: new gains = R=95, B=21; image = R=133.5, G=32, B=8\nStep 39: new gains = R=95, B=21; image = R=130.9, G=33.1, B=8\n\nSo at step 38, R went from 96 to 95.\nAt step 39, R stayed at 95.\n\nThis me