tput of step 38, not step 39!\n\nLet me re-read the log:\n```\n[09:52:43] ◇ 调整 #38: fine R=95 B=21 → R=133.5 G=32 B=8 (Δ=3.9213)\n[09:52:45] ◇ 调整 #39: done R=95 B=21 → R=130.9 G=33.1 B=8 (Δ=3.7094)\n```\n\nThe format is: `调整 #38: fine R=95 B=21 → R=133.5 G=32 B=8 (Δ=3.9213)`\n\nI think \"R=95 B=21\" is the gain AFTER the adjustment (the output of `step()`), and \"R=133.5 G=32 B=8\" is the image BEFORE the adjustment (the input to `step()`).\n\nSo at step 38, the algorithm chose R=95, B=21, and the image was R=133.5, G=32, B=8.\nAt step 39, the algorithm chose R=95, B=21, and the image was R=130.9, G=33.1, B=8.\n\nSo both step 38 and step 39 chose R=95, B=21.\n\nBut why? Let me recalculate for step 38.\n\nAt step 38:\n- Current gains: R=96, B=21 (from step 37)\n- Image: R=133.5, G=32, B=8\n\nCalculate `cr`:\n- `g_sum / r_sum * self._current_red = 32000 / 133500 * 96 = 0.240 * 96 = 23.0`\n- `int(23.0) = 23`\n- `23 - 96 = -73`\n- `max(-1, min(1, -73)) = -1`\n- `cr = 96 + (-1) = 95`\n\nCalculate `cb`:\n- `g_sum / b_sum * self._current_blue = 32000 / 8000 * 21 = 4.0 * 21 = 84`\n- `int(84) = 84`\n- `84 - 21 = 63`\n- `max(-1, min(1, 63)) = 1`\n- `cb = 21 + 1 = 22`\n\nCandidates:\n- Candidate 1: R=95, B=21\n- Candidate 2: R=96, B=22\n\nEvaluate candidate 1 (R=95, B=21):\n- `ar = 133500 * 95 / 96 = 132109`\n- `ab = 8000 * 21 / 21 = 8000`\n- `_eval = |132109/32000 - 1| + |8000/32000 - 1| = |4.13 - 1| + |0.25 - 1| = 3.13 + 0.75 = 3.88`\n\nEvaluate candidate 2 (R=96, B=22):\n- `ar = 133500 * 96 / 96 = 133500`\n- `ab = 8000 * 22 / 21 = 8381`\n- `_eval = |133500/32000 - 1| + |8381/32000 - 1| = |4.17 - 1| + |0.262 - 1| = 3.17 + 0.738 = 3.91`\n\nSo candidate 1 (R=95, B=21) is better (3.88 < 3.91). The algorithm correctly chose R=95, B=21.\n\nNow at step 39:\n- Current gains: R=95, B=21 (from step 38)\n- Image: R=130.9, G=33.1, B=8\n\nCandidates:\n- Candidate 1: R=94, B=21\n- Candidate 2: R=95, B=22\n\nEvaluate candidate 1 (R=94, B=21):\n- `ar = 130900 * 94 / 95 = 129520`\n- `ab = 8