{"type":"message","id":"4f864856","parentId":"89e0609e","timestamp":"2026-07-08T02:47:31.107Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to redesign the white balance algorithm. Let me first backup the current code, then implement the changes. I need to:\n\n1. Backup whitebalance.py\n2. Read the current whitebalance.py to understand the structure\n3. Modify IterativeWB class according to requirements\n4. Modify WhiteBalanceSearcher initialization\n5. Update version number\n\nLet me first read the current whitebalance.py to understand its structure, then make the modifications.\n\nActually, I already read whitebalance.py earlier in the conversation. Let me review the key parts:\n\n1. IterativeWB class - needs redesign\n2. WhiteBalanceSearcher class - needs to read current WB status and set initial values\n\nRequirements:\n1. Initial values: if already in WB mode, use current values; otherwise start from 50/50\n2. Step sizes based on delta: >10 → 5, 1-10 → 2, <1 → 1; no iteration limits\n3. When step=1, stop after 3 oscillations and revert to best\n4. Backup, version update, no new scripts/patches\n\nLet me backup first, then modify.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Copy-Item \"C:/Users/admin/.openclaw/agents/dev-factory/astrohub/src/controlpanel/whitebalance.py\" \"C:/Users/admin/.openclaw/agents/dev-factory/astrohub/backup_20260708_wb_redesign/whitebalance.py.bak\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":59264,"output":314,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59578,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783478835364,"responseId":"cht000d49ae@dx19f3f9f67ca29c2503"}}
