{"type":"message","id":"0aa00c4a","parentId":"2bc9b230","timestamp":"2026-07-08T02:47:43.904Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the current whitebalance.py code again and understand the full structure, then also check how the initial values are set (the entry point from the frontend).\n\nI need to:\n1. Modify initial value logic: if already in local WB mode or timed WB, keep current R/B; if switching from other mode, set 50/50\n2. Change step size logic: delta>10 → step 5; 1<delta<=10 → step 2; delta<1 → step 1; no step limits\n3. In step 1 phase: use oscillation detection like brightness - if 3 oscillations, restore best value; otherwise don't stop\n\nLet me also check the brightness.py for the oscillation pattern to understand what \"震荡3次\" means in the brightness context.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b565aee4e246438486023ef2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/admin/.openclaw/agents/dev-factory/astrohub/src/controlpanel/brightness.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":65084,"output":221,"cacheRead":27648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92953,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783478851526,"responseId":"chatcmpl-34ad2df4-9e91-9d7c-8eee-d7c9145a6bf7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b68d4a97","parentId":"0aa00c4a","timestamp":"2026-07-08T02:47:43.915Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b565aee4e246438486023ef2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"AstroHub v8.67 - 局部亮度控制模块\n\n算法：\n- IterativeBrightness: 纯算法迭代搜索（三阶优先级：快门→光圈→增益）\n- BrightnessSearcher: 执行层（截图、设置参数、验证、SSE事件）\n\n亮度计算：\n- Y = 0.299R + 0.587G + 0.114B（标准亮度）\n- 排除死黑死白 → 取有效像素Y均值 → 映射0-100\n\n调整逻辑：\n- 优先快门（每次1步opt_values档位）\n- 快门到极限 → 调光圈（每次1步opt_values档位）\n- 光圈快门都到极限 → 调增益（2阶段：±5粗调→±1精调）\n- 全部到极限 → 返回\"亮度不足\"或\"亮度超出\"\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport asyncio\nfrom .region_base import calc_brightness, calc_stable_delay\n\n\nclass IterativeBrightness:\n    \"\"\"亮度迭代搜索器 - 三阶优先级\n\n    优先级：快门 → 光圈 → 增益\n    快门/光圈：每次±1步（opt_values档位）\n    增益：2阶段（±5粗调 → ±1精调）\n    无步数限制，全部到极限时终止\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, target: float, shutter_idx: int, iris_idx: int,\n                 gain: int, shutter_values: list, iris_values: list,\n                 gain_min: int = 0, gain_max: int = 100):\n        self._target = target  # 0-100\n        self._shutter_values = shutter_values\n        self._iris_values = iris_values\n        self._gain_min = gain_min\n        self._gain_max = gain_max\n        self._tolerance = 0.5  # ±0.5 on 0-100 scale\n\n        self._shutter_idx = shutter_idx\n        self._iris_idx = iris_idx\n        self._gain = gain\n\n        # 增益阶段：1=粗调(±5), 2=精调(±1)\n        self._gain_phase = 1\n        self._gain_last_direction = 0  # 1=增, -1=减\n\n        # 振荡检测：亮度在目标上下交替超过N次 → 切换到下一参数\n        self._cross_count = 0  # 穿越目标次数\n        self._last_side = 0  # 1=高于目标, -1=低于目标\n        self._best_brightness = None  # 最接近目标的亮度\n        self._best_shutter_idx = shutter_idx\n        self._best_iris_idx = iris_idx\n        self._best_gain = gain\n        \n        # 参数锁定标记（振荡时锁定当前参数，切换到下一参数）\n        self._shutter_frozen = False\n        self._iris_frozen = False\n\n        # v8.68: 增益震荡检测\n        self._gain_osc_count = 0  # 增益震荡次数\n        self._gain_last_side = 0  # 上次在目标哪侧（1=高于, -1=低于）\n        self._best_gain_val = gain  # 震荡期间最佳增益\n\n        self._step_count = 0\n\n    def step(self, current_brightness: float) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"输入当前亮度(0-100)，返回下一步动作\"\"\"\n        self._step_count += 1\n        error = self._target - current_brightness\n        too_dark = error > 0\n\n        # 容差内 → 完成\n        if abs(error) <= self._tolerance:\n            return self._make_stop_result(\"done\", current_brightness,\n                f\"亮度达标 {current_brightness:.1f}≈{self._target}\")\n\n        # 振荡检测：跟踪亮度在目标上下穿越\n        current_side = -1 if too_dark else 1  # -1=低于目标, 1=高于目标\n        if self._last_side != 0 and current_side != self._last_side:\n            self._cross_count += 1\n        self._last_side = current_side\n\n        # 追踪最接近目标的参数值\n        if self._best_brightness is None or abs(error) < abs(self._target - self._best_brightness):\n            self._best_brightness = current_brightness\n            self._best_shutter_idx = self._shutter_idx\n            self._best_iris_idx = self._iris_idx\n            self._best_gain = self._gain\n\n        # === 优先级1: 快门 ===\n        if not self._shutter_frozen:\n            # 振荡检测：穿越目标2次 → 冻结快门，进入光圈\n            if self._cross_count >= 2:\n                self._shutter_frozen = True\n                self._shutter_idx = self._best_shutter_idx\n                self._cross_count = 0\n                self._last_side = 0\n                self._best_brightness = None\n                # fall through to iris\n            elif too_dark and self._shutter_idx > 0:\n                self._shutter_idx -= 1\n                return self._make_result(\"set_shutter\", current_brightness,\n                    f\"快门降档 {self._shutter_values[self._shutter_idx]}\")\n            elif not too_dark and self._shutter_idx < len(self._shutter_values) - 1:\n                self._shutter_idx += 1\n                return self._make_result(\"set_shutter\", current_brightness,\n                    f\"快门升档 {self._shutter_values[self._shutter_idx]}\")\n            # 快门到极限 → fall through to iris\n\n        # === 优先级2: 光圈 ===\n        if not self._iris_frozen:\n            # 振荡检测（仅当快门已冻结后生效）\n            if self._shutter_frozen and self._cross_count >= 2:\n                self._iris_frozen = True\n                self._iris_idx = self._best_iris_idx\n                self._cross_count = 0\n                self._last_side = 0\n                self._best_brightness = None\n                # fall through to gain\n            elif too_dark and self._iris_idx > 0:\n                self._iris_idx -= 1\n                return self._make_result(\"set_iris\", current_brightness,\n                    f\"光圈开大 F{int(self._iris_values[self._iris_idx])/100:.1f}\")\n            elif not too_dark and self._iris_idx < len(self._iris_values) - 1:\n                self._iris_idx += 1\n                return self._make_result(\"set_iris\", current_brightness,\n                    f\"光圈收小 F{int(self._iris_values[self._iris_idx])/100:.1f}\")\n            # 光圈到极限 → fall through to gain\n\n        # === 优先级3: 增益 ===\n        # v8.68: 增益震荡检测 - 连续3次穿越目标 → 回滚最佳值并成功\n        current_side = 1 if current_brightness > self._target else -1\n        if self._gain_last_side != 0 and current_side != self._gain_last_side:\n            self._gain_osc_count += 1\n            if self._gain_osc_count >= 3:\n                # 震荡3次，回滚到最佳增益\n                self._gain = self._best_gain_val\n                return self._make_stop_result(\"done\", current_brightness,\n                    f\"增益震荡{self._gain_osc_count}次，回滚最佳增益{self._gain}\")\n        self._gain_last_side = current_side\n\n        # 更新最佳增益（最接近目标的亮度）\n        if self._best_brightness is None or abs(current_brightness - self._target) < abs(self._best_brightness - self._target):\n            self._best_brightness = current_brightness\n            self._best_gain_val = self._gain\n\n        gain_step = 5 if self._gain_phase == 1 else 1\n        direction = 1 if too_dark else -1\n        new_gain = self._gain + gain_step * direction\n        new_gain = max(self._gain_min, min(self._gain_max, new_gain))\n\n        # 增益到极限\n        if new_gain == self._gain:\n            if self._gain_phase == 1:\n                # 粗调到极限 → 切换精调\n                self._gain_phase = 2\n                gain_step = 1\n                new_gain = self._gain + gain_step * direction\n                new_gain = max(self._gain_min, min(self._gain_max, new_gain))\n                if new_gain == self._gain:\n                    # v8.68: target=0/100碰到极限 = 成功完成\n                    if self._target == 0 or self._target == 100:\n                        return self._make_stop_result(\"done\", current_brightness,\n                            f\"目标极限，亮度={current_brightness:.1f}\")\n                    reason = \"亮度不足\" if too_dark else \"亮度超出\"\n                    return self._make_stop_result(reason, current_brightness,\n                        f\"{reason}(全部参数到极限)\")\n            else:\n                # v8.68: target=0/100碰到极限 = 成功完成\n                if self._target == 0 or self._target == 100:\n                    return self._make_stop_result(\"done\", current_brightness,\n                        f\"目标极限，亮度={current_brightness:.1f}\")\n                reason = \"亮度不足\" if too_dark else \"亮度超出\"\n                return self._make_stop_result(reason, current_brightness,\n                    f\"{reason}(全部参数到极限)\")\n\n        # 过冲检测：方向反转 → 切换精调\n        if self._gain_phase == 1 and self._gain_last_direction != 0:\n            if direction != self._gain_last_direction:\n                self._gain_phase = 2\n\n        self._gain_last_direction = direction\n        self._gain = new_gain\n        phase_name = \"粗调\" if self._gain_phase == 1 else \"精调\"\n        return self._make_result(\"set_gain\", current_brightness,\n            f\"增益{phase_name} {self._gain}\")\n\n    def _make_result(self, action: str, brightness: float, message: str) -> dict:\n        return {\n            \"action\": action,\n            \"step\": self._step_count,\n            \"brightness\": round(brightness, 1),\n            \"target\": self._target,\n            \"shutter\": self._shutter_values[self._shutter_idx],\n            \"iris\": self._iris_values[self._iris_idx],\n            \"gain\": self._gain,\n            \"gain_phase\": self._gain_phase,\n            \"message\": message\n        }\n\n    def _make_stop_result(self, reason: str, brightness: float, message: str) -> dict:\n        return {\n            \"action\": \"stop\",\n            \"reason\": reason,\n            \"step\": self._step_count,\n            \"brightness\": round(brightness, 1),\n            \"target\": self._target,\n            \"shutter\": self._shutter_values[self._shutter_idx],\n            \"iris\": self._iris_values[self._iris_idx],\n            \"gain\": self._gain,\n            \"steps\": self._step_count,\n            \"message\": message\n        }\n\n\nclass BrightnessSearcher:\n    \"\"\"亮度搜索执行器\n\n    复用白平衡模式：\n    - 每步：1读(截图) + 1写(设参数)\n    - 等待：calc_stable_delay()\n    - 中断：_interrupt()\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, mgr, device_ip, client, x, y, w, h, capture_func,\n                 cleanup_func, target, shutter_idx, iris_idx, gain,\n                 shutter_values, iris_values, gain_min=0, gain_max=100,\n                 mac_clean=\"\"):\n        self.mgr = mgr\n        self.device_ip = device_ip\n        self.client = client\n        self.x = x\n        self.y = y\n        self.w = w\n        self.h = h\n        self._capture_func = capture_func\n        self._cleanup_func = cleanup_func\n        self._mac_clean = mac_clean\n        self._interrupted = False\n        self._target = target\n        self._shutter_idx = shutter_idx\n        self._iris_idx = iris_idx\n        self._gain = gain\n        self._shutter_values = shutter_values\n        self._iris_values = iris_values\n        self._gain_min = gain_min\n        self._gain_max = gain_max\n        self._stable_delay = 1.5\n\n    def _set_shutter(self, level: str):\n        xml = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<Shutter version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n<ShutterLevel>{level}</ShutterLevel>\n</Shutter>'''\n        self.client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/Shutter\", xml)\n\n    def _set_iris(self, level: str):\n        xml = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<Iris version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n<IrisLevel>{level}</IrisLevel>\n</Iris>'''\n        self.client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/Iris\", xml)\n\n    def _set_gain(self, level: int, gain_limit: int = None):\n        xml = f'''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<Gain version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n<GainLevel>{level}</GainLevel>\n{'<GainLimit>' + str(gain_limit) + '</GainLimit>' if gain_limit is not None else ''}\n</Gain>'''\n        self.client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/gain\", xml)\n\n    def _set_exposure_manual(self):\n        xml = '''<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<Exposure version=\"2.0\" xmlns=\"http://www.hikvision.com/ver20/XMLSchema\">\n<ExposureType>manual</ExposureType>\n</Exposure>'''\n        self.client.put(\"/Image/channels/1/exposure\", xml)\n\n    def _capture(self):\n        bgr, crop_path, info = self._capture_func(\n            self.client, self.mgr, self.device_ip, \"Brightness\",\n            self.x, self.y, self.w, self.h,\n            skip_delay=True\n        )\n        return bgr, info\n\n    def _interrupt(self):\n        self._interrupted = True\n\n    async def run(self):\n        \"\"\"运行亮度搜索，产生SSE事件\"\"\"\n\n        # 读取快门延迟\n        self._stable_delay = await asyncio.to_thread(calc_stable_delay, self.client)\n\n        # 1. 切换手动曝光模式\n        await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_exposure_manual)\n\n        # 2. 初始截图\n        bgr, info = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n        if bgr is None:\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'error', 'message': '截图失败'})}\\n\\n\"\n            return\n\n        initial_brightness = calc_brightness(bgr) * 100.0 / 255.0\n\n        crop_msg = f\"X={info['crop_x1']}~{info['crop_x2']}, Y={info['crop_y1']}~{info['crop_y2']}, 共{info['pixels']}像素\"\n        yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'start', 'crop': crop_msg,\n                                    'initial_brightness': round(initial_brightness, 1),\n                                    'target': self._target})}\\n\\n\"\n\n        # 3. 创建迭代器\n        ib = IterativeBrightness(\n            self._target, self._shutter_idx, self._iris_idx, self._gain,\n            self._shutter_values, self._iris_values, self._gain_min, self._gain_max\n        )\n\n        # 4. 迭代循环\n        while True:\n            if self._interrupted:\n                cur_b = calc_brightness(bgr) * 100.0 / 255.0\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'interrupt', 'message': '用户停止',\n                                            'shutter': self._shutter_values[ib._shutter_idx],\n                                            'iris': f\"F{int(self._iris_values[ib._iris_idx])/100:.1f}\",\n                                            'gain': ib._gain,\n                                            'brightness': round(cur_b, 1)})}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n\n            cur_b = calc_brightness(bgr) * 100.0 / 255.0\n            cmd = ib.step(cur_b)\n\n            # SSE事件\n            event = {\n                \"type\": \"brightness\",\n                \"step\": cmd.get(\"step\", 0),\n                \"action\": cmd[\"action\"],\n                \"brightness\": cmd[\"brightness\"],\n                \"target\": cmd[\"target\"],\n                \"shutter\": cmd[\"shutter\"],\n                \"iris\": f\"F{int(cmd['iris'])/100:.1f}\",\n                \"gain\": cmd[\"gain\"],\n                \"gain_phase\": cmd.get(\"gain_phase\", 0),\n                \"message\": cmd[\"message\"]\n            }\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps(event)}\\n\\n\"\n\n            if cmd[\"action\"] == \"stop\":\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'done',\n                                            'final_brightness': cmd['brightness'],\n                                            'target': self._target,\n                                            'shutter': cmd['shutter'],\n                                            'iris': f\"F{int(cmd['iris'])/100:.1f}\",\n                                            'gain': cmd['gain'],\n                                            'total_steps': cmd['steps'],\n                                            'reason': cmd['reason']})}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n\n            # 应用参数（1写）\n            if cmd[\"action\"] == \"set_shutter\":\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_shutter, cmd[\"shutter\"])\n            elif cmd[\"action\"] == \"set_iris\":\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_iris, cmd[\"iris\"])\n            elif cmd[\"action\"] == \"set_gain\":\n                await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_gain, cmd[\"gain\"])\n\n            # 等待稳定\n            await asyncio.sleep(self._stable_delay)\n\n            # 重新截图（1读）\n            bgr, _ = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n            if bgr is None:\n                yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'error', 'message': '截图失败'})}\\n\\n\"\n                break\n\n        # 5. 清理\n        await asyncio.to_thread(self._cleanup_func, \"Brightness\", self.device_ip)\n        yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'cleanup'})}\\n\\n\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783478863915}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d510a0c","parentId":"b68d4a97","timestamp":"2026-07-08T02:49:41.040Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to redesign the white balance algorithm. Let me now also check how the white balance is called from the frontend and what the initial state looks like. I need to understand the current entry point.\n\nLet me also read the current whitebalance.py again to understand what needs to be changed.\n\nI've already read the whitebalance.py earlier. Let me now understand the key requirements:\n\n1. **Initial value logic**: \n   - If already in local WB mode or timed WB → use current R/B\n   - If switching from other mode → set 50/50\n\n2. **Step size logic (no iteration limits)**:\n   - delta > 10 → step 5\n   - 1 < delta <= 10 → step 2  \n   - delta < 1 → step 1\n\n3. **Stop condition when step=1**:\n   - Use oscillation detection like brightness: after 3 oscillations, restore to best value; otherwise don't stop\n\n4. **Development requirements**:\n   - Backup first\n   - Update version number\n   - No over-development\n   - Precise fix\n   - No new scripts or patches\n\nNow, I need to also check how the white balance search is called and where the \"local\" mode state is maintained. I should also read the router.py to understand the API endpoints.\n\nActually, let me focus on the core changes:\n\n1. Modify `IterativeWB` class in `whitebalance.py`\n2. Modify `WhiteBalanceSearcher` to handle initial value logic\n3. Update version in `constants.py`\n\nLet me first check if there's a \"local WB mode\" state or flag I need to read. Let me check the frontend or API to understand how local WB is triggered.\n\nActually, let me re-read the whitebalance.py more carefully to understand the current code structure and what needs to change.\n\nFrom what I read earlier:\n\nCurrent `IterativeWB`:\n- `__init__(self, current_red=100, current_blue=100)` - takes initial values\n- `_stage_steps = [5, 2, 1]` - fixed stages\n- `_stage_thresholds = [100, 10, 0.1]` - thresholds to advance stages\n- `_fine_steps = 0` - counts fine steps, stops at 20\n- `_best_red`, `_best_blue`, `_best_delta` - track best values\n- `_eval()` - evaluates candidate\n- `step()` - generates next step\n\nCurrent `WhiteBalanceSearcher`:\n- `_read_wb_status()` - reads current mode and gains\n- If mode is \"auto\" → starts at 50/50\n- If mode is locked/manual → uses current values\n\nNow the user's requirements:\n\n1. **Initial value**:\n   - If already in local WB mode (or timed WB state) → use current values\n   - If switching from other mode → set 50/50\n   - Need to add a parameter to distinguish between \"already in WB mode\" and \"just switched to WB mode\"\n   \n   Actually, looking at the code, the `_read_wb_status()` reads the current mode. If it's manual/locked, it uses current values. If it's auto, it uses 50/50.\n   \n   The user's requirement is:\n   - If the device was already in local WB mode (manual/locked with current WB settings) → keep current values\n   - If switching from other mode (auto) → set 50/50\n   \n   This is almost what the current code does, but the issue is that when the device is already in manual mode with R=95, B=21, the algorithm starts from there and gets stuck.\n   \n   So the initial value logic should be:\n   - If device is in manual/locked mode → use current values (but check if they make sense, i.e., 50-200 range)\n   - If device is in auto mode → set 50/50\n\n2. **Step size**:\n   - delta > 10 → step 5\n   - 1 < delta <= 10 → step 2\n   - delta < 1 → step 1\n   - No stage limits\n\n3. **Stop condition when step=1**:\n   - Oscillation detection: if delta oscillates 3 times around the best value, restore to best and stop\n   - Otherwise continue (no step limit)\n\nLet me redesign the algorithm:\n\n```python\nclass IterativeWB:\n    def __init__(self, current_red=100, current_blue=100):\n        self._current_red = current_red\n        self._current_blue = current_blue\n        \n        # Track best\n        self._best_red = current_red\n        self._best_blue = current_blue\n        self._best_delta = 999.0\n        \n        # Oscillation tracking for fine phase (step=1)\n        self._osc_count = 0\n        self._last_direction = 0  # 1=improving, -1=worsening\n        self._fine_phase = False\n        \n        self._step_count = 0\n\n    def step(self, bgr) -> dict:\n        stats = _rgb_stats(bgr)\n        n = stats[\"n\"]\n        r_sum, g_sum, b_sum = stats[\"r_sum\"], stats[\"g_sum\"], stats[\"b_sum\"]\n        \n        self._step_count += 1\n        \n        # Calculate delta\n        actual = abs(r_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0)\n        \n        # Determine step size based on current delta\n        if actual > 10:\n            step = 5\n        elif actual > 1:\n            step = 2\n        else:\n            step = 1\n            self._fine_phase = True\n        \n        # Update best\n        if actual < self._best_delta:\n            self._best_delta = actual\n            self._best_red = self._current_red\n            self._best_blue = self._current_blue\n        \n        # Generate candidates\n        # Calculate target values\n        cr = self._current_red + max(-step, min(step, int(g_sum / max(1, r_sum) * self._current_red) - self._current_red))\n        cb = self._current_blue + max(-step, min(step, int(g_sum / max(1, b_sum) * self._current_blue) - self._current_blue))\n        cr = max(1, min(255, cr))\n        cb = max(1, min(255, cb))\n        \n        # Choose candidate\n        candidates = []\n        if step == 1:\n            candidates = [(cr, self._current_blue, \"red\"), (self._current_red, cb, \"blue\")]\n        else:\n            candidates = [(cr, cb, \"both\"), (cr, self._current_blue, \"red\"), (self._current_red, cb, \"blue\")]\n        \n        best_cand = None\n        best_d = 999.0\n        for r, b, label in candidates:\n            d = self._eval(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, r, b)\n            if d < best_d:\n                best_d = d\n                best_cand = (r, b, label)\n        \n        new_red, new_blue, direction = best_cand\n        new_red = int(new_red)\n        new_blue = int(new_blue)\n        \n        # Oscillation detection for fine phase\n        if self._fine_phase and step == 1:\n            # Check if we're oscillating around best\n            current_eval = self._eval(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, self._current_red, self._current_blue)\n            new_eval = self._eval(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, new_red, new_blue)\n            \n            if new_eval > current_eval:\n                # Worsening\n                self._osc_count += 1\n                if self._osc_count >= 3:\n                    # Restore best and stop\n                    return {\n                        \"action\": \"stop\",\n                        \"stage\": \"fine\",\n                        \"step_size\": 1,\n                        \"red_gain\": self._best_red,\n                        \"blue_gain\": self._best_blue,\n                        ...\n                    }\n            else:\n                # Improving - reset oscillation count? Or keep it?\n                # In brightness, it tracks crossings. Let me think...\n                pass\n        \n        # Normal step\n        self._current_red = new_red\n        self._current_blue = new_blue\n        \n        return {\n            \"action\": \"continue\",\n            \"red_gain\": new_red,\n            \"blue_gain\": new_blue,\n            ...\n        }\n```\n\nWait, I need to think more carefully about the oscillation detection. In the brightness algorithm, oscillation is detected by \"crossing the target\" (brightness going above and below the target). For white balance, the \"target\" is delta=0, so oscillation would be delta going above and below the best delta.\n\nBut actually, in the brightness algorithm, oscillation is when the brightness crosses the target value (goes from below to above or vice versa). For white balance, we don't have a target delta - we want to minimize delta. So oscillation would be when the algorithm goes back and forth around the minimum.\n\nActually, let me re-read the brightness oscillation logic:\n```python\ncurrent_side = 1 if current_brightness > self._target else -1\nif self._gain_last_side != 0 and current_side != self._gain_last_side:\n    self._gain_osc_count += 1\n    if self._gain_osc_count >= 3:\n        # 震荡3次，回滚到最佳增益\n        self._gain = self._best_gain_val\n        return self._make_stop_result(\"done\", ...)\nself._gain_last_side = current_side\n```\n\nSo for brightness, oscillation is defined as crossing the target (brightness goes from below to above or vice versa). For white balance, the \"target\" is delta=0, but delta can't go below 0. So oscillation would need to be defined differently.\n\nActually, the user's requirement says \"以局部亮度同样的算法，震荡3次时恢复到最佳值\". The \"局部亮度\" algorithm tracks when brightness crosses the target. For white balance, we could track when the delta goes above and below the best delta. But since delta can only decrease (we're minimizing), the oscillation would be when the algorithm tries to adjust but delta increases instead of decreases.\n\nActually, a better interpretation: in the fine phase (step=1), if the algorithm tries to adjust R or B but the delta gets worse, that's an oscillation. After 3 such oscillations (trying to improve but getting worse), restore to the best value and stop.\n\nWait, but the user said \"震荡3次时恢复到最佳值\". Let me think about what \"震荡\" means in the context of the brightness algorithm.\n\nIn brightness:\n- Target is a fixed value (e.g., 50)\n- Algorithm adjusts gain up/down\n- When brightness crosses the target (goes from below to above or vice versa), that's a \"crossing\"\n- After 3 crossings, the algorithm restores to the best value and stops\n\nFor white balance:\n- Target is delta=0 (minimum)\n- Algorithm adjusts R/B\n- \"震荡\" would be when the algorithm overshoots the minimum and delta starts increasing\n\nBut wait, in the brightness algorithm, the oscillation is about crossing the target, not about overshooting the minimum. The target is a fixed point, and the algorithm oscillates around it.\n\nFor white balance, if we want to use the same logic, we could define a \"target delta\" (e.g., 0.1 or some small value) and track when delta crosses this target. But that doesn't make much sense.\n\nAlternatively, \"震荡\" could mean the algorithm keeps going back and forth between two states. For example:\n- Step N: R=95, delta=3.7\n- Step N+1: R=94, delta=3.8 (worse)\n- Step N+2: R=95, delta=3.7 (back to previous)\n\nThis would be an oscillation. After 3 such oscillations, restore to best and stop.\n\nActually, let me re-read the user's requirement more carefully:\n\"在1步进的时候，以局部亮度同样的算法，震荡3次时恢复到最佳值，否则不停止。\"\n\n\"局部亮度同样的算法\" - the brightness algorithm uses \"crossing the target\" as the oscillation criterion. But for white balance, the target is not fixed.\n\nI think the user's intent is:\n- In the fine phase (step=1), if the algorithm keeps oscillating (going back and forth between similar values without improving), after 3 oscillations, restore to the best value found and stop.\n- If there's no oscillation, keep going (no step limit).\n\nLet me implement this by tracking the direction of improvement:\n\n```python\n# Track oscillation\ncurrent_eval = self._eval_for_current(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum)\nnew_eval = self._eval(r_sum, g_sum, b_sum, new_red, new_blue)\n\nif new_eval >= current_eval:\n    # Not improving\n    self._no_improve_count += 1\nelse:\n    # Improving\n    self._no_improve_count = 0\n\nif self._fine_phase and self._no_improve_count >= 3:\n    # Oscillated 3 times, restore best\n    return stop with best values\n```\n\nBut this is different from the brightness algorithm. The brightness algorithm tracks \"crossing the target\", not \"not improving\".\n\nActually, I think the user might mean something simpler. Let me re-read the brightness algorithm's oscillation logic:\n\nIn brightness:\n```python\ncurrent_side = 1 if current_brightness > self._target else -1\nif self._gain_last_side != 0 and current_side != self._gain_last_side:\n    self._gain_osc_count += 1\n    if self._gain_osc_count >= 3:\n        self._gain = self._best_gain_val\n        return stop\nself._gain_last_side = current_side\n```\n\nFor white balance, we could define:\n- `current_side = 1 if current_delta > target_delta else -1` (target_delta = 0.1 or some small value)\n- Track crossings of target_delta\n\nBut this doesn't quite fit. The brightness algorithm has a specific target value. White balance wants to minimize delta without a specific target.\n\nLet me think differently. The user said \"震荡3次时恢复到最佳值\". In the context of optimization, \"震荡\" means the algorithm keeps oscillating around the minimum without converging. For example:\n- R=95, delta=3.7\n- R=94, delta=3.8 (worse)\n- R=95, delta=3.7 (back)\n- R=94, delta=3.8 (worse again)\n\nThis is 2 oscillations (95→94→95→94). After 3 such oscillations, stop.\n\nActually, I think the simplest interpretation is:\n- In the fine phase (step=1), if the delta stops improving for 3 consecutive steps, restore to the best value and stop.\n- This is essentially \"no improvement for 3 steps\" = oscillation.\n\nWait, but the user specifically said \"以局部亮度同样的算法\". Let me look at the brightness algorithm again.\n\nIn the brightness algorithm, the oscillation is specifically about crossing the target. The target is the desired brightness. When brightness crosses the target (goes from below to above or vice versa), that's a crossing. After 3 crossings, the algorithm assumes it's oscillating around the target and restores to the best value.\n\nFor white balance, if we want the same logic, we need a \"target\" to cross. The obvious target is delta=0, but delta can't go below 0. So we'd need to define a target delta (e.g., 0.1).\n\nActually, let me just implement a simpler version that matches the user's intent:\n- In the fine phase (step=1), track when the algorithm changes direction (i.e., delta starts increasing after decreasing, or vice versa).\n- After 3 such direction changes (oscillations), restore to the best value and stop.\n\nThis is a reasonable interpretation of \"震荡3次\".\n\nLet me also think about the step size logic more carefully:\n\nCurrent logic (to be replaced):\n- 3 stages: coarse (step=5), medium (step=2), fine (step=1)\n- Stage thresholds: 100, 10, 0.1\n\nNew logic:\n- Delta > 10 → step = 5\n- 1 < delta <= 10 → step = 2\n- Delta < 1 → step = 1\n- No stage limits\n\nThis means the step size is dynamic based on current delta, not fixed stages. The algorithm could go from step 5 to step 2 to step 1 as delta decreases, and even back to step 5 if delta increases.\n\nWait, but if delta increases (e.g., due to a bad step), should the step size increase? The user's requirement doesn't specify. I think the simplest implementation is:\n- Calculate delta from current image\n- Set step based on delta\n- Generate candidates with that step\n- Choose best candidate\n- If step=1, check oscillation\n\nThis is simpler and more robust than the current stage-based approach.\n\nNow, about the initial value logic. The user said:\n\"1. 当切换到局部白平衡模式，如果之前已经是局部白平衡模拟，或者是定时白平衡启动的状态，R B初始值从当前开始。如果是从其他模式切换到局部白平衡模式，初始值在切换到局部白平衡的时候就设置50 50。\"\n\nI need to understand how the frontend distinguishes between \"already in local WB\" and \"switching to local WB\". \n\nLooking at the current code in `WhiteBalanceSearcher.run()`:\n```python\n# 1. 读取当前模式+增益（v8.62）\ncurrent_mode, current_red, current_blue = await asyncio.to_thread(self._read_wb_status)\n\n# 2. 切换到手动白平衡模式\nok = await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_mode, \"manual\")\nif not ok:\n    yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'warning', 'message': '切换手动白平衡失败'})}\\n\\n\"\n\n# 3. 初始值判断\nif current_mode == \"auto\":\n    # 自动模式 → 从50/50起步，写入设备\n    current_red, current_blue = 50, 50\n    await asyncio.to_thread(self._set_wb_gains, 50, 50)\n    yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'info', 'message': '初始值: R=50, B=50'})}\\n\\n\"\nelse:\n    # locked/manual 模式 → 从当前值开始（保留上次结果/手动设置）\n    yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'info', 'message': f'初始值: R={current_red}, B={current_blue}'})}\\n\\n\"\n```\n\nThe current code already does this: if mode is auto, start from 50/50; otherwise use current values.\n\nBut the user's requirement is more nuanced: \"如果之前已经是局部白平衡模拟，或者是定时白平衡启动的状态，R B初始值从当前开始。\"\n\nThis seems to be about whether the user is already in the white balance mode (e.g., just did a search and is doing another one) vs. switching from other modes.\n\nIn the frontend, there might be a \"local WB mode\" that the user can toggle on/off. When they toggle it on, if they were already in WB mode, use current values. If switching from another mode, set 50/50.\n\nBut looking at the current code, this is already handled by the `current_mode` check. If the device is already in manual/locked mode, it means the user was already in some kind of manual WB, so use current values. If the device is in auto mode, set 50/50.\n\nThe user's requirement seems to match the current logic, but maybe they want it to be more explicit. Let me check the frontend code to see if there's a \"local WB mode\" toggle.\n\nActually, I think the user wants me to make sure the initial value logic is correct. Let me re-read the requirement:\n\n\"当切换到局部白平衡模式，如果之前已经是局部白平衡模拟，或者是定时白平衡启动的状态，R B初始值从当前开始。如果是从其他模式切换到局部白平衡模式，初始值在切换到局部白平衡的时候就设置50 50。\"\n\nI think \"局部白平衡模拟\" and \"定时白平衡启动\" refer to the frontend states where the user has already triggered a white balance search (either immediately or scheduled). In these cases, the device is already in manual WB mode with some R/B values, so the next search should start from those values.\n\n\"如果是从其他模式切换到局部白平衡模式\" means the user just turned on the local WB mode from the frontend, and the device is in auto or some other mode. In this case, set 50/50.\n\nThe current code does this by checking `current_mode`. If the device is in manual/locked, use current values. If auto, use 50/50.\n\nI think the user's intent is already mostly implemented. The issue is that when the device is in manual mode with R=95, B=21, the algorithm starts from there and gets stuck. The user wants to fix the algorithm, not the initialization.\n\nBut the user explicitly asked for the initialization logic too. Let me make sure it's correct.\n\nActually, I think there's a subtle difference. The current code reads the device state. The user wants the initial state to depend on the FRONTEND state (whether the user is already in local WB mode or just switched to it). \n\nBut this is a frontend concern. The backend just reads the device state. If the frontend wants to start from 50/50, it can explicitly set the device to auto mode before calling the backend.\n\nActually, looking at the code flow:\n1. Frontend calls the API\n2. Backend reads device state\n3. Backend decides initial values\n\nThe frontend might not have a way to communicate \"I'm already in WB mode\" vs \"I just switched to WB mode\". The backend can only read the device state.\n\nI think the user wants me to keep the current initialization logic (which is already correct) and focus on the algorithm changes.\n\nWait, let me re-read: \"如果是从其他模式切换到局部白平衡模式，初始值在切换到局部白平衡的时候就设置50 50。\"\n\nThis might mean: when the user clicks the \"local WB\" button (not \"scheduled\" or \"immediate\"), set 50/50. But the backend doesn't know how the search was triggered.\n\nI think the user's intent is already covered by the current code. Let me focus on the algorithm changes.\n\nNow let me also check the version number. I need to update it.\n\nLet me read constants.py to see the current version.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.read:9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/admin/.openclaw/agents/dev-factory/astrohub/src/main/constants.py"}}],"api":