{"type":"message","id":"98c4d248","parentId":"c7d335ab","timestamp":"2026-07-08T03:26:26.563Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to fix two issues in brightness.py:\n\n1. Oscillation stop should only trigger during fine phase (step=1), not during coarse phase\n2. Initial values for brightness search should come from device (read current exposure params), not from frontend request\n\nAlso: delete outdated code after fixing.\n\nLet me analyze the code carefully.\n\n**Issue 1: Oscillation only during fine phase (step=1)**\n\nCurrent code (lines ~132-142):\n```python\n# v8.68: 增益震荡检测 - 连续3次穿越目标 → 回滚最佳值并成功\ncurrent_side = 1 if current_brightness > self._target else -1\nif self._gain_last_side != 0 and current_side != self._gain_last_side:\n    self._gain_osc_count += 1\n    if self._gain_osc_count >= 3:\n        self._gain = self._best_gain_val\n        return self._make_stop_result(\"done\", current_brightness,\n            f\"增益震荡{self._gain_osc_count}次，回滚最佳增益{self._gain}\")\nself._gain_last_side = current_side\n```\n\nThis check runs BEFORE the phase switch logic (lines 152-160). So it runs during coarse phase too.\n\nFix: Add `if self._gain_phase == 2:` to only check during fine phase.\n\n**Issue 2: Initial values from device**\n\nThe BrightnessSearcher gets initial values from the constructor, which comes from the frontend request. The user wants initial values to be read from the device.\n\nI need to add methods to read current shutter/iris/gain from the device in BrightnessSearcher.run(), before creating IterativeBrightness.\n\nFor reading from ISAPI:\n- Shutter: GET /Image/channels/1/Shutter → `<ShutterLevel>...</ShutterLevel>`\n- Iris: GET /Image/channels/1/Iris → `<IrisLevel>...</IrisLevel>`\n- Gain: GET /Image/channels/1/gain → `<GainLevel>...</GainLevel>`\n\nThen I need to convert the device values to indices in the respective arrays.\n\nActually wait - let me re-read the user's request more carefully:\n\n\"现在检查亮度调整局部亮度调整的逻辑\n1. 我需要实现的，最终3次震荡3次后应用最佳，并且是在增益以1为步进的情况下实现，现在实际没有实现。\n2. 自动白平衡的初始值，必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个数值开始。现在实际增益不是这么操作的。\"\n\nFor issue 1: oscillation detection should only apply when gain step is 1 (fine phase). Currently it runs regardless of phase.\n\nFor issue 2: the user mentions \"自动白平衡\" (automatic white balance) but then talks about aperture/shutter/gain. This is definitely a typo - they mean the brightness search initial values should come from the device's current exposure parameters.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read. \"自动白平衡的初始值，必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个数值开始\" - they literally say \"automatic white balance's initial values must start from current aperture, shutter, gain\".\n\nBut white balance doesn't use aperture/shutter/gain. It uses R/B gain. I think the user is saying: \"the initial values for automatic [brightness] must come from the current aperture, shutter, gain values.\"\n\nActually, I think they might be talking about the local brightness adjustment feature. The initial values for brightness search should be the current exposure settings from the device.\n\nOK, let me just implement both fixes precisely.\n\nLet me also think about what \"删除过期代码\" means. The user probably wants me to remove outdated comments or dead code after fixing.\n\nLet me implement:\n\n1. Move oscillation check to after the phase switch, and add `if self._gain_phase == 2:` guard\n2. Add `_read_exposure_params()` method to BrightnessSearcher that reads current shutter/iris/gain from device\n3. Call it in run() before creating IterativeBrightness\n\nFor reading ISAPI:\n- Shutter: GET /Image/channels/1/Shutter\n- Iris: GET /Image/channels/1/Iris  \n- Gain: GET /Image/channels/1/gain\n\nThe responses contain XML with specific elements. I need to parse them.\n\nActually, looking at the existing code, I see that _set_shutter, _set_iris, _set_gain all write to these endpoints. So the reading endpoints should be the same.\n\nLet me implement the _read_exposure_params method. I'll need to:\n1. GET /Image/channels/1/Shutter → find ShutterLevel element\n2. GET /Image/channels/1/Iris → find IrisLevel element\n3. GET /Image/channels/1/gain → find GainLevel element\n\nThen convert to indices in the shutter_values and iris_values arrays.\n\nFor shutter and iris, the values are strings like \"1/100\" or \"1000\". I need to find the index of these values in the arrays.\n\nFor gain, it's a numeric value.\n\nLet me now implement the fixes.\n\nActually, I need to be careful about what \"删除过期代码\" means. Let me look for any dead code or outdated comments that should be removed.\n\nLet me now write the fix. I'll:\n1. Move oscillation check to only run during fine phase (after the phase switch at line ~153)\n2. Add _read_exposure_params() to BrightnessSearcher\n3. Update run() to read current params before starting\n\nFor the oscillation fix, I need to move the check block to after the gain_phase switch (around line 153), and add a guard `if self._gain_phase == 2:`.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The user said \"增益以1为步进的情况下实现\". This means the oscillation detection should only trigger when the gain step is 1 (i.e., during fine phase).\n\nSo the fix is to add `if self._gain_phase == 2:` around the oscillation check block.\n\nBut where should I move it? Currently it's at the top of the gain section. I should move it to after the phase switch check, because only after the phase switch do we know we're in fine phase.\n\nActually, the oscillation check needs to run AFTER we know the phase. The phase is determined at initialization (phase 1 = coarse) and switches to phase 2 (fine) when certain conditions are met.\n\nThe phase switch happens at lines 153-160:\n```python\nif self._gain_phase == 1:\n    # 粗调到极限 → 切换精调\n    self._gain_phase = 2\n```\n\nThis happens when `new_gain == self._gain` (at limit during coarse phase).\n\nSo the oscillation check should be moved to after this block, with a guard `if self._gain_phase == 2:`.\n\nLet me implement this now.\n\nActually, I realize there's a subtlety. The oscillation check currently happens BEFORE the gain is updated. If I move it to after the phase switch, the flow would be:\n\n1. Calculate new_gain\n2. Check if at limit (phase switch)\n3. Check oscillation (if fine phase)\n4. Update gain\n\nBut the oscillation is detected by comparing current_brightness > target. This needs to happen BEFORE the gain is applied, not after.\n\nActually, the oscillation check is comparing the current brightness (after the previous gain was applied) with the target. So it should run before the new gain is calculated.\n\nLet me keep the oscillation check where it is but add the phase guard. The question is: what if we're in coarse phase? The oscillation should be ignored.\n\nOK, the simplest fix is to add `if self._gain_phase == 2:` around the oscillation check block. This way, during coarse phase, the oscillation is ignored.\n\nBut wait, there's another issue. The oscillation check updates `self._gain_last_side` every iteration. If we're in coarse phase, `self._gain_last_side` will be updated but no oscillation is detected. Then when we switch to fine phase, the last side might be stale.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach is:\n1. Keep the oscillation tracking (updating gain_last_side) running all the time\n2. Only trigger the stop when `self._gain_phase == 2` and `self._gain_osc_count >= 3`\n\nThis way, during coarse phase, we still track the oscillations but don't stop. Once we enter fine phase, if there have been 3 oscillations, we stop immediately.\n\nHmm, but that might not be what the user wants. The user might want the oscillation count to reset when entering fine phase.\n\nActually, I think the user's intent is simpler: \"在增益以1为步进的情况下实现\" - the oscillation stop should only be implemented when gain step is 1. This means:\n- During coarse phase (step=5): ignore oscillation, don't track it\n- During fine phase (step=1): track oscillation, stop after 3 crossings\n\nSo I should move the oscillation tracking AND detection inside the fine phase guard.\n\nActually, let me re-read the user's message one more time:\n\n\"1. 我需要实现的，最终3次震荡3次后应用最佳，并且是在增益以1为步进的情况下实现，现在实际没有实现。\"\n\n\"I need to implement: finally 3 oscillations → apply best, and this should be implemented when gain step is 1. Currently this is not actually implemented.\"\n\nSo the user is saying that the oscillation detection is not working as intended. Let me look at why.\n\nLooking at the code flow:\n1. Lines 134-141: Oscillation check - if 3 crossings → stop\n2. Lines 143-145: Update best gain\n3. Line 147: Calculate gain_step (5 or 1)\n4. Lines 148-149: Calculate new_gain\n5. Lines 151-161: Check if at limit (phase switch)\n6. Lines 168-171: Overshoot detection (coarse → fine)\n7. Lines 173-175: Update gain_last_direction, gain\n\nThe problem: the oscillation check at lines 134-141 runs BEFORE the phase switch at lines 151-161. So during coarse phase (step=5), if there are 3 oscillations, it would stop immediately. But the user wants it to only stop during fine phase (step=1).\n\nWait, but the user says \"现在实际没有实现\" - \"currently this is not actually implemented\". So maybe the oscillation detection is not working at all?\n\nLet me trace through the code more carefully.\n\nThe oscillation check:\n```python\ncurrent_side = 1 if current_brightness > self._target else -1\nif self._gain_last_side != 0 and current_side != self._gain_last_side:\n    self._gain_osc_count += 1\n    if self._gain_osc_count >= 3:\n        ...\nself._gain_last_side = current_side\n```\n\nWait, I see the issue! `self._gain_last_side` is initialized to 0. The check `self._gain_last_side != 0` means the first time this runs, it won't increment the count. That's fine.\n\nBut then `self._gain_last_side = current_side` is set to either 1 or -1. So subsequent iterations will work correctly.\n\nActually, I think the code works but the problem is that it runs during coarse phase too. The user wants it to ONL