">\n<GainLevel>{level}</GainLevel>\n</Gain>'''\n```\n\nOK, so the GET responses should have ShutterLevel, IrisLevel, GainLevel elements.\n\nNow I need to convert the device values to indices. For shutter and iris, the values are strings that might need to be matched against the arrays.\n\nFor example, if the device returns \"1/100\" and the shutter_values array is [\"1/1000\", \"1/500\", \"1/100\", ...], I need to find the index of \"1/100\".\n\nFor gain, it's a numeric value. If the device returns 50, I use that directly.\n\nLet me implement this.\n\nActually, let me also think about error handling. If the read fails, I should fall back to the constructor values.\n\nOK, let me now write the complete fix.\n\nActually, I realize I should also check if `resp.xml` exists. Let me look at the client implementation...\n\nActually, let me just use `resp.text` instead of `resp.xml` to be safe. No wait, the existing code uses `resp.xml`. Let me check if this is a custom attribute...\n\nActually, in the hikvision ISAPI client, `resp` might be a custom response object with a `.xml` attribute. Let me just use the same pattern as the existing code.\n\nOK let me now implement the fixes. I'll:\n1. Move oscillation check to fine phase only\n2. Add _read_exposure_params() to BrightnessSearcher\n3. Call it in run() before creating IterativeBrightness\n4. Remove outdated code\n\nLet me write the edit commands.\n\nFor the oscillation fix, I need to:\n- Wrap the oscillation check with `if self._gain_phase == 2:`\n- Reset oscillation tracking when entering fine phase\n- Also reset when overshoot detection triggers fine phase\n\nFor the initial values fix, I need to:\n- Add _read_exposure_params() method\n- Call it in run() before creating IterativeBrightness\n- Update self._shutter_idx, self._iris_idx, self._gain\n\nLet me write the edits now.\n\nActually, I also need to update the version number. Currently it's v8.70 (from the white balance fix). I should update to v8.71.\n\nLet me plan