lf._gain_osc_count += 1\n    if self._gain_osc_count >= 3:\n        ...\nself._gain_last_side = current_side\n```\n\nThis ran unconditionally (both phases). With ±5 steps, it could oscillate too quickly and stop prematurely. Now I've restricted it to phase 2 only.\n\nBut there's another issue: when in phase 1 (coarse ±5), the `_gain_last_side` and `_gain_osc_count` are not being updated. So when we transition to phase 2, the oscillation detection starts fresh. That's correct.\n\nWait, but there's still a problem. When `_gain_phase == 1`, the oscillation detection block is skipped entirely, which means `_gain_last_side` is NOT updated during phase 1. When we enter phase 2, `_gain_last_side` is still 0 (or whatever it was when phase 1 ended). This means the first oscillation in phase 2 won't be detected because `_gain_last_side` needs to be non-zero first.\n\nActually, looking at the code: `self._gain_last_side` is initialized to 0 and is only updated in the oscillation detection block. But now that block is inside `if self._gain_phase == 2:`, so during phase 1, `_gain_last_side` stays at 0. When we enter phase 2, the first check `if self._gain_last_side != 0` will be False, so it won't count as an oscillation. It will just set `_gain_last_side = current_side`. Then the next time, if the side changes, it will count. This is actually correct behavior.\n\nBut wait, there's also the over冲检测 code below:\n```python\nif self._gain_phase == 1 and self._gain_last_direction != 0:\n    if direction != self._gain_last_direction:\n        self._gain_phase = 2\n```\n\nThis sets `_gain_phase = 2` when direction reverses during phase 1. But `_gain_last_direction` is updated at the bottom:\n```python\nself._gain_last_direction = direction\n```\n\nSo when we transition to phase 2, `_gain_last_direction` has the last direction from phase 1. That's fine.\n\nOK so the first fix (oscillation only in phase 2) looks correct. Let me verify the second issue.\n\n> 2. 自动白平衡的初始值，必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个