the boss is talking about the brightness search's initial values. Let me re-read:\n\n> 2. 自动白平衡的初始值，必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个数值开始。现在实际增益不是这么操作的。\n\nHmm, \"自动白平衡\" = auto white balance. But \"光圈、快门、增益\" = iris, shutter, gain. These are exposure parameters, not white balance parameters.\n\nI think the boss might mean: \"自动亮度\" (auto brightness) initial values must start from current iris, shutter, gain values. And the gain is not actually doing this.\n\nLet me check the router.py code to see how the brightness search is called and what initial values are passed.\n\nFrom router.py line 4335-4354:\n```python\ntarget = float(data.get(\"target\", 50))\nshutter_idx = int(data.get(\"shutter_idx\", 0))\niris_idx = int(data.get(\"iris_idx\", 0))\ngain = int(data.get(\"gain\", 0))\nshutter_values = data.get(\"shutter_values\", [])\niris_values = data.get(\"iris_values\", [])\ngain_min = int(data.get(\"gain_min\", 0))\ngain_max = int(data.get(\"gain_max\", 100))\n\nsearcher = BrightnessSearcher(\n    ...\n    target=target, shutter_idx=shutter_idx, iris_idx=iris_idx,\n    gain=gain, shutter_values=shutter_values, iris_values=iris_values,\n    gain_min=gain_min, gain_max=gain_max\n)\n```\n\nThe initial values come from the frontend. If the frontend sends gain=0, then the search starts from gain=0. The boss says the initial values should come from the current device state.\n\nBut wait, the frontend should be reading the current device state and sending those values. Let me check if there's an issue with how the frontend gets the current gain value.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be simpler. Let me re-read the boss's message:\n\n> 2. 自动白平衡的初始值，必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个数值开始。现在实际增益不是这么操作的。\n\nI think the boss is saying: \"The auto-brightness initial values must start from the current iris, shutter, gain. But the gain is not actually doing this.\"\n\nMaybe the issue is that the gain starts from 0 (or some default) instead of the current device gain. This would be a frontend issue, not a backend issue.\n\nBut the boss asked me to fix the backend code. Let me check if there's a way to read the current device exposure settings in the backend and use those as initial values.\n\nActually, looking at the BrightnessSearcher.run() method, it doesn't read the current device state. It just uses the values passed from the frontend. If the frontend sends wrong values, the search will start from wrong values.\n\nBut the boss said \"修复，禁止过度开发\" - fix it, no over-development. So I should just make sure the backend correctly uses the values passed from the frontend.\n\nActually, I think I'm overthinking this. Let me re-read the boss's requirements:\n\n> 1. 我需要实现的，最终3次震荡3次后应用最佳，并且是在增益以1为步进的情况下实现，现在实际没有实现。\n\nThis is about the oscillation detection. I've already fixed this by restricting it to phase 2.\n\n> 2. 自动白平衡的初始值，必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个数值开始。现在实际增益不是这么操作的。\n\nWait, I just realized - the boss might be talking about the WHITE BALANCE initial values, not brightness. Let me re-read:\n\n\"自动白平衡的初始值\" = auto white balance initial values\n\"必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个数值开始\" = must start from current iris, shutter, gain\n\nBut white balance doesn't use iris, shutter, gain. White balance uses R/B gain values.\n\nI think the boss is confused about terminology, or I'm misunderstanding. Let me just focus on what I can fix:\n\n1. Oscillation detection in brightness - DONE (restricted to phase 2)\n2. Initial values for brightness search - need to check if the frontend is sending correct values\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the boss's original message more carefully:\n\n> 现在检查亮度调整局部亮度调整的逻辑\n> 1. 我需要实现的，最终3次震荡3次后应用最佳，并且是在增益以1为步进的情况下实现，现在实际没有实现。\n> 2. 自动白平衡的初始值，必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个数值开始。现在实际增益不是这么操作的。\n\nThe boss says \"检查亮度调整局部亮度调整的逻辑\" - check the brightness adjustment logic. Then point 2 says \"自动白平衡的初始值\" - auto white balance initial values.\n\nI think the boss made a typo and meant \"自动亮度的初始值\" (auto brightness initial values). The mention of \"光圈、快门、增益\" confirms this - these are exposure/brightness parameters.\n\nSo the issue is: the brightness search should start from the current device's iris, shutter, gain values. But the gain is not actually starting from the current value.\n\nLooking at the code, the initial values are passed from the frontend. If the frontend sends the correct current values, the backend should use them correctly. The backend code looks correct - it just uses the values passed in.\n\nSo the issue might be on the frontend side. But the boss asked me to fix the backend. Let me check if there's a way to read the current device state in the backend before starting the search.\n\nActually, I think the simplest fix is to have the BrightnessSearcher read the current device exposure settings before starting the search, and use those as initial values if the frontend didn't provide them.\n\nBut the boss said \"禁止过度开发\" - no over-development. So I should just make sure the existing code works correctly.\n\nLet me look at the code flow again:\n\n1. Frontend sends POST /vision/brightness-search with target, shutter_idx, iris_idx, gain, etc.\n2. Router creates BrightnessSearcher with those values\n3. BrightnessSearcher.run() creates IterativeBrightness with those values\n4. IterativeBrightness uses those values as starting point\n\nThe issue might be that the frontend is sending gain=0 or some default, and the backend should be reading the current device gain instead.\n\nBut reading the current device state requires ISAPI calls, which the BrightnessSearcher doesn't currently do. Adding that would be \"over-development\" according to the boss.\n\nActually, I think the boss's point is simpler. Let me re-read:\n\n> 2. 自动白平衡的初始值，必须从当前的光圈、快门、增益三个数值开始。现在实际增益不是这么操作的。\n\n\"现在实际增益不是这么操作的\" - \"the gain is not actually doing this\"\n\nMaybe the issue is that the gain adjustment in the brightness search doesn't start from the current gain, but from 0 or some other default. Let me check the IterativeBrightness constructor:\n\n```python\ndef __init__(self, target: float, shutter_idx: int, iris_idx: int,\n             gain: int, shutter_values: list, iris_values: list,\n             gain_min: int = 0, gain_max: int = 100):\n    ...\n    self._gain = gain\n```\n\nThe initial gain is passed in. If the frontend sends the correct current gain, this should work.\n\nI think the issue might be that the frontend is not sending the correct current gain. But I can't fix the frontend without the boss's approval.\n\nLet me just report what I've found and what I've fixed, and ask the boss for clarification on point 2.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the boss's message one more time:\n\n> 修复，禁止过度开发，修复完成删除过期代码\n\n\"修复完成删除过期代码\" - \"after fixing, delete obsolete code\"\n\nSo the boss wants me to:\n1. Fix the issues\n2. Delete obsolete code\n\nLet me look for obsolete code in brightness.py. The `_gain_last_direction` variable is used for over冲 detection (switching from phase 1 to phase 2). Is that still needed?\n\nActually, looking at the code, the over冲 detection is:\n```python\nif self._gain_phase == 1 and self._gain_last_direction != 0:\n    if direction != self._gain_last_direction:\n        self._gain_phase = 2\n```\n\nThis switches from coarse (±5) to fine (±1) when the direction reverses. This is still needed.\n\nBut wait, the boss's requirement was:\n> 在增益以1为步进的情况下实现\n\n\"implement with gain step=1\"\n\nSo the boss wants the oscillation detection to only happen when gain step is 1 (phase 2). I've already done this.\n\nBut the boss also said the oscillation detection is \"现在实际没有实现\" (not actually implemented). Let me check if there's a bug in the oscillation detection logic.\n\nLooking at the original code:\n```python\n# === 优先级3: 增益 ===\n# v8.68: 增益震荡检测 - 连续3次穿越目标 → 回滚最佳值并成功\ncurrent_side = 1 if current_brightness > self._target else -1\nif self._gain_last_side != 0 and current_side != self._gain_last_side:\n    self._gain_osc_count += 1\n    if self._gain_osc_count >= 3:\n        # 震荡3次，回滚到最佳增益\n        self._gain = self._best_gain_val\n        return self._make_stop_result(\"done\", current_brightness,\n            f\"增益震荡{self._gain_osc_count}次，回滚最佳增益{self._gain}\")\nself._gain_last_side = current_side\n```\n\nThis runs for both phases. With phase 1 (±5 steps), the brightness can oscillate wildly, causing `_gain_osc_count` to reach 3 quickly, and the search stops prematurely before even entering phase 2.\n\nMy fix restricts this to phase 2 only:\n```python\n# === 优先级3: 增益 ===\n# v8.70: 增益震荡检测 - 只在精调阶段（步长=1）检测\nif self._gain_phase == 2:\n    current_side = 1 if current_brightness > self._target else -1\n    if self._gain_last_side != 0 and current_side != self._gain_last_side:\n        self._gain_osc_count += 1\n        if self._gain_osc_count >= 3:\n            # 震荡3次，回滚到最佳增益\n            self._gain = self._best_gain_val\n            return self._make_stop_result(\"done\", current_brightness,\n                f\"增益震荡{self._gain_osc_count}次，回滚最佳增益{self._gain}\")\n    self._gain_last_side = current_side\n```\n\nThis should fix issue 1.\n\nFor issue 2, I need to understand what the boss means. Let me just report my findings and ask for clarification.\n\nActually, I just realized something. The boss said \"自动白平衡的初始值\" but then mentioned \"光圈、快门、增益\". Maybe the boss is talking about the white balance search's initial values needing to account for the current exposure settings?\n\nNo, that doesn't make sense. White balance and exposure are independent.\n\nI think the boss made a typo and meant \"自动亮度\" (auto brightness). The issue is that the brightness search's initial gain value is not starting from the current device gain.\n\nBut looking at the code, the initial gain IS passed from the frontend. If the frontend sends the wrong value, that's a frontend bug.\n\nUnless... the boss wants the backend to read the current device state and use those values, regardless of what the frontend sends?\n\nLet me just report what I've done and ask for clarification on point 2.\n\nActually, I just realized I should also check if there's any obsolete code to delete. The boss said \"修复完成删除过期代码\".\n\nLooking at the brightness.py code, I see some potentially obsolete code:\n- `_gain_last_direction` is used for over冲 detection, which switches from phase 1 to phase 2. This is still needed.\n- `_gain_phase` is used to track coarse/fine phase. This is still needed.\n- `_gain_osc_count` and `_gain_last_side` are used for oscillation detection. These are still needed.\n\nI don't see any obviously obsolete code to delete.\n\nLet me just report my findings to the boss.\n\nWait, I should also check if the oscillation detection fix actually works. Let me trace through the logic:\n\n1. Phase 1 (coarse ±5): oscillation detection is skipped. `_gain_last_side` stays at 0.\n2. Direction reverses → `_gain_phase = 2` (fine ±1)\n3. Phase 2 (fine ±1): oscillation detection runs.\n4. First step in phase 2: `_gain_last_side` is 0, so `if self._gain_last_side != 0` is False. Just set `_gain_last_side = current_side`.\n5. Second step: if side changed, `_gain_osc_count` becomes 1. If not, stays 0.\n6. Continue until `_gain_osc_count >= 3` → stop and restore best.\n\nThis looks correct.\n\nBut wait, there's an issue. When we transition from phase 1 to phase 2, `_gain_last_side` is 0. The first step in phase 2 sets `_gain_last_side` but doesn't count as an oscillation. This is correct.\n\nBut what if the direction reverses multiple times during phase 1? Each reversal resets `_gain_last_direction` but doesn't affect `_gain_last_side`. So when we enter phase 2, `_gain_last_side` is still 0. This is correct.\n\nOK, I think the fix is correct. Let me report to the boss.\n\nActually, I realize I should also update the version number and create a backup. Let me do that.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e09735860721403280998027","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:/Users/admin/.openclaw/agents/dev-factory/astrohub && mkdir -p backup_20260708_brightness_osc"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5f592ab3668a450ab81c88e3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Copy-Item \"C:/Users/admin/.openclaw/agents/dev-factory/astrohub/src/controlpanel/brightness.py\" \"C:/Users/admin/.openclaw/agents/dev-factory/astrohub/backup_20260708_brightness_osc/brightness.py.bak\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":110644,"output":4779,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115423,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783481698513,"responseId":"chatcmpl-f1d788a0-928d-9569-9f72-06ff07b3ded6"}}
